title: beer-cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into 2-quart greased casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together and pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Remove from heat and cover with grated cheese.

title: veggie chili
directions: In large pot, saute the onions and green pepper in the oil over medium heat until onions are browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir so vegetables do not burn.
Stir in the mustard seed, chili powder, cumin, cocoa, cinnamon, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the beans, water, salt and Tabasco.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 40 minutes or until the chili has thickened.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Serves 6.

title: whatsit
directions: Slice muffins into halves.
Place under broiler until lightly browned.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread on muffins. Return to the broiler until cheese melts and becomes golden.
Each muffin may also be quartered to serve.
You can also make up ahead of time and store in freezer.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: bittermint truffles
directions: Combine cream, vanilla and salt in a medium saucepan.
Cook at medium heat to a gentle boil.
(Stir frequently.) Remove from heat and cool for 5 minutes.
Melt chocolate, taking care not to scorch (break chocolate into small pieces before melting).
Whisk the egg yolk and melted chocolate into creamy mixture.
Add cognac and peppermint.
Stir in butter, blend well.
Cool to room temperature. Freeze overnight.
Form into 1 inch balls using melon baller.
(Use the powdered sugar to coat the melon baller and hands to prevent sticking.)
Freeze balls for 2 hours.
Dip balls into melted cover chocolate and place on wax paper until cooled.
Use fork or knife edge to decorate tops of Truffles.

title: garlic cheese spread
directions: Allow cheese to soften.
Add garlic powder and sour cream. Mix well and refrigerate.
Flavor becomes stronger as it sits. Keeps well.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Beat with fork
until smooth.
Make batter even in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top
with
nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix each of the 3 boxes of jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water in separate bowls.
Put each in shallow pans; chill until firm. Cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Put all colors together and toss.
Mix the lime jello with 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Let this stand until it becomes syrupy, then mix with the Cool Whip.
Add to jello squares; toss until covered.
Pour into cooked pie shells. Makes 2 pies.
Great for Easter.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 1-quart baking dish. Place frozen broccoli in dish. Add cubed cheese. Spoon undiluted soup over broccoli and cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple rings
directions: Peel the apples; with an apple corer, remove the core, leaving apple whole.
Slice the apple crosswise in rings about 1/2-inch thick.
Make a batter with the flour, milk, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Use enough milk to make the batter thick enough to cling to the apple slices.
Dip each apple ring in the batter and place in hot shortening.
Fry until brown on both sides and apple is tender. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour in 9 x 12-inch pan, covered.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
No peeking!

title: pineapples coolers
directions: In a blender add pineapple, pineapple juice, and coconut extract. Blend tell smooth. Then add 2 cubes of ice at a time and blend well. Serve in a tall glass.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs. In skillet over medium-low heat in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove; keep warm.
Pour off fat.
In skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chicken with parslied rice.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes if desired.
Serves 4.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash the rice.
Mix meat, onion, rice and seasonings in a bowl.
Form into balls.
Place in frying pan and brown.
Add soup and water.
Cover and braise 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Layer greased (Pam) tray with saltines. Boil butter and brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour onto saltines; bake in oven for 5 minutes (do not overcook).
Melt and pour chocolate chips on top; spread with knife.
Sprinkle with nuts and enjoy!!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish in order listed, except put corn flakes in melted butter and spread on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until potatoes are hot.

title: jewel marmalade
directions: Grind the peaches, oranges and cherries together using medium blade.
Measure.
For each 4 cups of pulp, add 3 cups of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of Kitchen-Klatter almond flavoring.

title: tomato bacon squares
directions: Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion with food chopper.
Mix all ingredients except biscuits.
Set aside.
Separate each biscuit into 2 thinner halves.
Press biscuit halves into bottom of the muffin tin.
Put mixture into biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° or until puffed and brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo, oil, sugar, eggs (add one at a time), flour, baking powder, milk and coconut flavor.
After mixing all ingredients well, fold in 1 can Angel Flake coconut.
Do not stir coconut with mixer.
Use spoon.
Grease tube pan well.
I use Pam, then dust with flour, remove excess flour.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with Marshmallow Creme and then add Cool Whip. (I prefer using strawberry flavored cream cheese.)

title: cauliflower soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine onion and margarine and cook, stirring until onion is tender.
Cut cauliflower into florets. Add to pan with carrot, broth and water.
Cover and cook until cauliflower is tender.
Cool slightly, then puree in blender or food processor.
Return to pan. Stir in milk and seasonings. Reheat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place all ingredients (except paprika) in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in order given.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° until chicken is done and water has been absorbed.
One of our family's favorites!

title: southwestern stuffed peppers
directions: Stem and seed pepper halves.
Cook in boiling salted water for 3 minutes; drain.
Place cut side up in shallow baking dish. Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Add tomatoes, water, barbecue sauce and salt; bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix in corn.
Spoon mixture into pepper halves.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: key west crab bisque
directions: Boil crab and lobster.
Pick out meat and reserve 2 1/2 cups broth.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef slowly in oven or on stove top, crumbling and separating with fork.
Drain off all grease and add onion powder and seasoned salt.
Set aside.

title: microwave mochi
directions: Mix together; put in circular microwave tube pan.
Cook on High for
minutes
if
in a carousel microwave.	If not, cook for
minutes on High; stop and turn 180° and cook another 3
minutes on High.
Turn out and cool.
Sprinkle with mochiko and cut.

title: dilly beans
directions: Clean green beans and stuff them in pint jars, get as many in the jar as you can.
To each jar put garlic, cayenne pepper, garlic cloves and dill.
Boil water, salt and vinegar; pour into jar.
If jars are hot before you stuff them they will seal better. Let set for two weeks before eating.

title: margery's sweet relish
directions: Let stand overnight; rinse well.
Make syrup.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix ground beef, bell pepper, onion, celery salt, egg and oats together.
Make hamburger patties.
Bake at 350° until done; drain.
Pour can of soup over patties; add 1/2 can of water.
Put back in oven and cook for about 10 more minutes.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Gradually add milk and blend.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks and mix.
Stir egg yolk mixture into remaining hot mixture.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla extract.
Cool slightly and pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Top with sweetened whipped cream or 3 egg whites meringue.
A 3 1/2 ounce package of pudding and pie mix may be substituted for this basic cream filling.
Use either an 8 or 9-inch pie shell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash with salted water and cook until tender.
Remove from heat, drain well.
Mash with potato masher.
Combine remaining ingredients with squash mixture and pour in a greased casserole dish.
Top with crumbs made with leftover cornbread. Sprinkle with poultry seasoning and onion powder.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: quick spiced peaches
directions: Drain syrup from peaches into saucepan.
Add sugar, cider vinegar and pickling spices.
Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes. Add peaches and simmer gently 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and chill, allowing fruit to stand in spiced syrup several hours or overnight.
Serve as garnish or meat accompaniment.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Marinate steaks in Italian dressing for 2 hours. Brush fish with oil and cook 5 to 7 minutes on each side.

title: bran muffins
directions: *For sour milk, take 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar plus sweet milk to make 1 cup.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine water, sugar and coffee and simmer about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and vodka and allow to cool.

title: seattle salmon pie with cucumber sauce
directions: Mix eggs, milk, butter, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Break salmon in chunks and remove bones and skin.
Stir salmon into egg mixture.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Roll pastry 1/8-inch, cut into 8-inch circle, then cut into 6 wedges.
Arrange on top of pie.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes.

title: beef and cheese bake
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water until tender, 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
In a skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter; saute onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef and cook until brown. Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa, chiles, green onions and cheese well and refrigerate overnight.
Spread mix over the whole tortilla. Roll real tight.
Wrap tightly in Saran Wrap and refrigerate. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Can be frozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop kraut finely.
Add all together, then add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir all together.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa thoroughly.
Add milk; stir until creamy.
Add vanilla and butter; cook until it almost thickens (about 30 minutes).
Take pan off heat; sit it in cold water, stirring constantly, to cool.
Pour into a large, buttered pan or plate; let it harden.
(You may want to put it in the freezer.)

title: quick sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat corn oil in skillet.
Brown pork.
Add next six ingredients and bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes or until done. Mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water; add to pork with green pepper.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.

title: holy bible cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This cake will keep indefinitely in a covered pan.
This recipe is over 100 years old.

title: breakfast take alongs
directions: Beat together the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until well blended.
Add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, cheese, wheat germ and bacon.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 14 minutes, or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.
Store in loosely covered container in refrigerator or at room temperature. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.
Good when camping and hiking.

title: mock slim trim sour cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Serve as substitute for sour cream.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a large plastic bag.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, a few at a time, and add to flour mixture in bag.
Shake well to coat completely.
Shake off excess flour. Heat oil in large pan over medium heat.
Brown chicken, turning once, 5 minutes or until golden.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook, turning several times, for 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices are no longer pink when thigh (or dark meat) is pierced.
Uncover and increase heat to high.
Cook about 2 minutes until crispy, turning once.
Drain on paper towels. Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch slices
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each. Add nuts and flavorings. Add flour.
Mix well.
Shape in 2-inch rolls or small loaves and roll in wax paper. Chill overnight or until firm enough to slice.
Cut 1/8-inch slices. Bake on an ungreased baking sheet in hot oven at 425° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: cranapple walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour and dry ingredients.
Add to the first mixture and stir until combined. Stir in apples, cranberries and nuts.
Bake in a well greased 9 x 13 pan for 45-50 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce, eggs and cracker crumbs.
Add to ground beef.
Shape into a loaf.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake from cake mix
directions: Whisk together cake and pudding mixes.
Add rest of ingredients at medium speed. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and serve cold.

title: lemon pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour together, then add eggs, then the lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients until crumbly. Spread in 9 x 12 greased pan; pat down.

title: lemon lust
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Stir in flour and spread on bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown. Let cool completely.

title: grape wine
directions: The other day a friend of mine gave me a sack of home grown tomatoes and asked that I sample them.
Now the only way to sample a tomato is to make a tomato sandwich.

You need some fresh sandwich bread, not whole wheat, not rye, but white loaf bread. Coat two sides with mayonnaise, either homemade or Hellmann's. Slice the tomato in 1/2-inch slices and cover the bread.
Give a generous dashing of salt and pepper.
Mmmmmm delicious.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Place oyster crackers in large deep pan. Warm the oil and sprinkle over crackers. Toss well. Mix dry ingredients well and sprinkle over crackers, stir to coat. Bake 250° for one hour, stirring once or twice. Store in an airtight container.

title: fantastic pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Butter a deep pie pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Finely grate the lemon rind (reserve lemon) and add to bread batter.
Stir flour with salt and soda and add alternately with buttermilk.
Pour batter into two lightly greased and floured 9 x 3-inch bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread springs back to the touch.

title: polish cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumbers and slice very thin.
Salt and leave standing for 30 minutes so that the water is drawn from the cucumbers.
Place in a napkin and squeeze out the liquid.
Pepper and mix sour cream.
Yoghurt may be substituted for sour cream. Also you can add sweet onions if you so desire.

title: carrot ginger soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepot.
Add onions and gently cook until transparent, approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
Add carrots, ginger and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Strain, reserving broth.
Puree vegetables in a blender.
Return vegetables and broth to saucepot. Stir in orange juice, milk and cream.
Return to heat.
Season with salt and a dash of paprika; do not boil.
Serve with dollop of sour cream and a sprinkling of chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Roll out crescent rolls in one piece.
Spread in bottom of dish and press together.
Cover with meat and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over all you made.
Add onion or green pepper to taste, before adding milk. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Spread in bottom of 2-quart or 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, onion, mayonnaise and eggs and pour over broccoli in the casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta, pepper and broccoli salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as label directs, but do not use salt in the water. Drain; keep warm.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine coconut, chopped pecans and oleo.
Toast under broiler until brown, stirring frequently.
Combine first 3 ingredients and spread half of the mixture in a pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut-pecan mixture over this and drizzle with caramel topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels, milk and butter.
Add pecan halves.
Drop onto buttered waxed paper.
After they harden, dip into melted chocolate and return them to waxed paper.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Put cheese in a microwaveable bowl.
Add chili.
Microwave on High for 9 minutes (stir halfway through cooking time).
Stir again before serving.
Serve with a big bowl of Doritos.

title: turkey-bacon salad
directions: Mix the turkey, bacon, cauliflower and radishes in 2 1/2-quart bowl.

title: holiday delight candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and cream.
Place over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Beat about 8 minutes or until thick and light color.
Add vanilla, fruit and nuts gradually.
Mixture will be thick and sticky.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Let cool 24 hours until firm.
Wrap in foil.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Combine crab, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 8 to 30 minutes at 400°. Serve hot with Triscuits or rice crackers.
Yum!

title: cambridge chicken
directions: Brown the chicken in small amount of fat.
(Electric pan preferred.) Remove chicken from pan. Slice off in small pieces the outside of 1 lemon (1 lemon for 4 pieces of chicken).
Put in bottom of frypan.
Place chicken back in pan. Sprinkle each piece of chicken with rosemary and pour 1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar over each piece.
Cook until done.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce, sugar and onion.
Separate biscuits and place each one in an ungreased muffin cup.
Press dough up sides to edges.
Spoon meat into each.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.
Yield:
3 cups of spread.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the pecans and coconut and spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan sprayed with Pam.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts. Grease and flour 2 small loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Check with toothpick.

title: parmesan zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini into very thin slices.
Simmer zucchini slices in 1/2 inch water in a nonstick skillet.
Drain.
Spread mixture onto nonstick baking sheet (or use Pam); sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, syrup and vanilla.
Beat again.
Dip bread in mixture.
Fry in a small amount of butter or margarine. Lightly sprinkle with cinnamon on one side of bread before frying.

title: spiced meat balls and vegetables
directions: Combine beef, onion, green peppers, corn meal, milk, egg, chili powder and other seasonings.
Shape into 12 balls and roll in flour.
Melt shortening in skillet; brown meat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour, catsup and water.
Place in Dutch oven; add vegetables and cover.
Cook until vegetables are done, about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat 3 eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini. In another bowl, mix all other ingredients, then combine with eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini mixture.
Pour into 3 small or 2 large greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Bon appetit.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Prepare cabbage leaves for stuffing.
Season the meat with salt and pepper.
Add grated onion and rice.
Roll a portion of the meat mixture in each leaf.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place cabbage rolls, folded sides down, with the rest of the ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Add a little water and simmer for 1 hour.
Add sugar and vinegar, if needed, to adjust seasoning.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Mix together gelatine, pineapple, water and sugar; boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 large or 2 (3-ounce) packages cream cheese; stir until dissolved.
Add the canned cream and nuts.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit loops
directions: Crush Fruit Loops; set aside.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Put margarine, sugar and vanilla into mixing bowl. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in Fruit Loop crumbs. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Place mixed vegetables, celery and onions in saucepan.

Cook until tender. Drain and add Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise and sugar. Stir well. Place in 2-quart baking dish. Mix together Ritz crackers and melted margarine. Sprinkle on top of vegetables; bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: diet cake
directions: Cook raisins and water until dry.
Mix together applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil.
Blend in flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, soda and nuts.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: italian egg balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil.
Mix until smooth.
Heat oil in frypan until hot.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into oil and brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 18 balls.

title: spinach salad
directions: Shake together.
Pour over salad just before serving.

title: suzy q's
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and water.
Sift all dry ingredients all at once.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Bake 5 minutes at 475°.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: light lemon cheesecake
directions: Prep. and baking time:
About 1 hour.
Chilling time:
2 hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and set aside.
Saute onion in 1/2 cup bacon fat.
Blend in with onion all remaining ingredients (except potatoes and bacon) and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and bacon. Serve warm.

title: classic american pot roast
directions: Coat beef with mixture of flour, salt, sugar and pepper. Brown on all sides in hot oil in large Dutch oven.
When beef is turned, add onions and saute until tender.
Add broth and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Cover, then simmer 2 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery and turnips.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender.
(Or cook in slow cooker following manufacturer's directions.)
Discard bay leaf.
Slice meat and serve with vegetables and sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole, layer Doritos, chicken, onions and cheese.
Repeat 2 layers.
Combine soups, chicken broth and tomatoes.
Pour over layers.
Bake in 400° oven until casserole bubbles all over about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza bread
directions: Can add other stuffing ingredients to taste.

title: shrimp veracruz
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Mix all and bake at 350 degrees until done.
Mix salad shrimp if desired and sunflower seeds are optional.

title: apple cheese ball
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, cheddar cheese and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in apples.
Shape mixture into balls.
Roll ball around in nuts until completely covered.
Insert cinnamon stick and bay leaf on top of ball to resemble stem and leaf of apple.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly with moistened hands, shape into loaf and place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: meat spread for sandwiches
directions: Boil eggs to hard, then cool.
Grind the beef, add eggs, pickles, onions and celery.
Grind everything.
Mix in a large bowl, salt and pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip or mayonnaise. Mix all.
Refrigerate.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until thick and add corn.
Combine flour, sugar and salt; add to corn mixture.
Add milk and butter and blend thoroughly.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in 325° oven about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Stir from bottom twice during baking period.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare noodles according to package; drain.
In large skillet, melt butter and cook mushrooms over medium heat until tender.
Stir in flour.
Blend in water, milk, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in pimento, which has been drained. Fold in noodles and chicken.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, egg and onion; stir well.
Carefully drop batter by tablespoon into deep hot oil. Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry only until golden brown; drain well on absorbent paper.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
If using electric skillet, oil should be 370°.

title: venison meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, water chestnuts, soy sauce, ginger and garlic. Crumble the venison and sausage over the mixture and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. In a skillet over medium heat, brown meatballs in batches in 2 teaspoons oil, adding 1 teaspoon oil as needed. Transfer meatballs to a slow cooker. In the same skillet, saute mushrooms in 1 teaspoon oil until tender. Add the broth and 1 cup wate; :pour over the meatballs. Cover and cook on low for 4-5 hours. Remove meatballs and mushrooms with a slotted spoon, keep warm. Strain cooking juices into a saucepan. Combine cornstarch and remaining water until smooth, add to saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over the meatballs, mushrooms and noodles. Yield: 8-10 servings.

title: peg's peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients to a hard ball stage (when dropped in a cup of cold water, forms a ball).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir until thick.
Pour into a well buttered pan.
Slice while still warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing and butter; line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1/2 of dressing mixture. Save the remaining 1/2 for the top. Mix all other ingredients. Pour over dressing.
Cover with remaining dressing mix. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove cover and brown top.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Microwave sugar and syrup 2 1/2 minutes, stir and microwave another 2 1/2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and stir. Then add rice krispies. Let mixture cool a little while and then add M & M's. Pour into 9 x 13 pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Slightly steam broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit overnight refrigerated.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes; sieve.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir in milk. Cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly add hot tomato mixture, stirring constantly.
Serves 6.

title: "no crust" apple pie
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples and pecans.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef, then add soup and wine.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours. Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4.
May use crock-pot.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Place popped corn in large roasting pan. Let stand in oven while preparing glaze.

title: hog maw salad
directions: Turn maw inside out and expose seam lined with a ridge of white fat.
Pull or trim off fat from seam and anywhere else you see it.
Wash maw in cold water 3 times.
Put maw in pot; cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Take maw out and throw water away.
Cut maw into small pieces (1/2-inch).
Put back in pot; cover with new water.
Cook at a slow boil for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours until chewable.
Cool maw.
Add lemon juice and all other spices except red pepper.
Mix and chill.
Serve on romaine. Sprinkle on red pepper.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt jello with hot water, then add the next 3 ingredients. Mix and chill.
Top with sour cream.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add the zucchini, crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Mix lightly; spoon vegetable mixture into a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Cover; bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes; bake 10 minutes longer.
Top with Cheddar cheese before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in uncooked shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Separately combine stuffing mix and butter. Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Combine eggs, mustard and salt.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in cheese, sausage and bread.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold linguine salad
directions: Boil linguine per directions on box and cool.
Slice up veggies.
Mix linguine with 3/4 bottle of Zesty Italian dressing and half a bottle of Salad Supreme.
Then add all of your vegetables and mix well.
Then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix well with wet ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until center is done.

title: snow salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot milk.
Let cool.
Add whipped topping to beat.
Cut drained orange slices into small pieces to add to mixture, along with drained pineapple.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon into dish and refrigerate.

title: corn fritters
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, beat egg; add sugar, Bisquick and milk; mix well.
Add corn, blend well.
Fry in Crisco oil.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut in small pieces the beef, veal, pork, celery and onions. Put large piece of butter in kettle and melt.
Add beef and cook 15 minutes with cover on, then 15 minutes with the cover off.
Add veal and cook 15 minutes with cover on, then 15 minutes with cover off.
Add pork and cook 15 minutes with cover on, then 15 minutes with cover off.
Add celery and cook 15 minutes with cover on and 15 minutes with the cover off.
Add onions and cook 15 minutes with the cover on and then 15 minutes with the cover off.
Add La Choy sauce to taste and as many mushrooms as you want.
When all done, add 1/2 cup hard molasses with 3 tablespoons cornstarch stirred in. Add bean sprouts (1 can) or La Choy vegetables.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Brown in skillet with salt and pepper.
Combine browned meat, tomato sauce and water in slow cooker.
Cook on low until meat is tender (6 to 8 hours).
Add peas 1 hour before serving.

title: homemade butter
directions: Let heavy cream set out of refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Pour heavy cream into quart jar and shake vigorously for 15 to 20 minutes. Soon you will see the butter taking shape.
Pour off the sweet milk that remains after butter is formed.
Spread butter on bread or saltines and enjoy.
You may drink the milk that remains.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Pour pie filling into the bottom of an 11 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle
cake
mix
on
top of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon and pecans
over
the
mix.
Melt
the butter and drizzle over the top.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: chewy peanut bars
directions: Cream together the shortening, peanut butter, eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Then stir in coconut.
Bake about 25 minutes in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: green tomatoes parmesan
directions: Lightly sprinkle tomatoes with salt; drain on paper towel for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Boil pasta for 12 minutes, put in strainer and set aside.
Cut up cucumber, tomato and shred lettuce.
Whip together mayonnaise and vinegar, add salt and pepper.
Put pasta, vegetables and dressing in a big bowl and mix.
Chill before serving.

title: squash piddle
directions: Layer vegetables with salt and ice.
Let stand at least three hours.
Boil sugar, vinegar, seed and turmeric.
Add drained vegetables.
Bring back to boil.
Put in jars and seal.
Process in water bath for 15 minutes, simmering.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Marinate artichokes in dressing to which Parmesan cheese has been added.
(Marinate overnight or all day.)
When ready to serve, toss dressing with lettuce, oranges and croutons.
Do not mix until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Add the flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts.
Work together real good. Spread over bottom of dish (large, oblong baking dish).
Cook until light brown at 350°.
Set aside to cool.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Mix onions and liverwurst.
I form into mound shape on serving dish and refrigerate until firm.
Mix cream cheese, Tabasco sauce and mayonnaise.
Spread cream cheese mixture over liverwurst mound and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Combine the bean juice, brown sugar, mustard, catsup and molasses.
Stir into beans.
Cover top with bacon strips (can partially cook bacon first, to keep it from splattering in oven). Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese soup
directions: Place diced potatoes, onions, celery, carrots, bouillon cubes and water in a large pot.
Simmer until vegetables are soft. Remove from heat.
Place in food processor or blender to puree vegetables.
Return to large pot.
Add diced cheese to soup. Simmer until cheese has melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated or freeze until ready to heat and serve.

title: yellow squash casserole 5
directions: Cook squash with onion.
Melt margarine in 8-inch baking dish. Tilt dish to coat sides of dish. Pour into crumbs and mix.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour squash mixture into dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: self-rising cornmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered can and use soon.
Use in any recipe calling for self-rising cornmeal.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and coconut. Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.

Sprinkle salmon chunks over bottom of pastry shell. Combine cream cheese and lemon juice. Gradually beat in reserved liquid from salmon, adding salt and cream. Beat the egg yolks lightly and stir into cream cheese mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry. Fold gently into egg yolk, cream cheese mixture.
Spoon over salmon and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
May garnish with pimento, if desired.
Very rich!
Good for brunch.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Bake 350 or 375 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate squares.
Stir in sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle marshmallows, chocolate chips, nuts and M&M's.
Continue baking 3 to 5 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook for 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a large bowl.
They don't have to be thawed completely but break up any large chunks.
Add Velveeta cheese, mayonnaise, green onions, salt and pepper; mix well.
Chop the pound of bacon and saute.
Should not be crisp; drain.
Put potato mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and cover with the bacon. Cook, uncovered, in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until hot in middle.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to beef.
Let simmer until thick, about 1/2 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: amaretto yams
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, Amaretto, vanilla and salt.
Add sweet potatoes and 1/4 cup juice from sweet potatoes.
Mash and cook sweet potatoes until thoroughly heated.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with more marshmallows and chopped pecans.

title: easy chocolate mousse
directions: Place chocolate pudding in mixing bowl.
Pour milk into the pudding mix and stir.
Then put the whole container of Cool Whip in the pudding mixture and stir until smooth.
Then refrigerate.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and grated rind.
Chill mixture until congealed; beat until fluffy. Beat well chilled milk until stiff.
Add to jello mixture.
Spread half of crumbs in the bottom of a 7 x 9-inch pan.
Add mixture. Top with remaining crumbs.

title: golden punch
directions: Bring sugar and 4 cups water almost to a boil.
Add the jello; let cool.
Add undiluted frozen lemonade and orange juice.
Add the cans of pineapple juice, 1 gallon water and almond extract. Freeze.
Before serving, add 1 1/2 quarts ginger ale and the partially frozen pineapple juice.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Lightly mix together the bread crumbs, onion, margarine, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each drop.
Blend soup and the 1/3 can of water; pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix altogether except noodles.
Put half of noodles in bottom of lightly greased casserole.
Add well mixed chicken and veggies. Place rest of noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: busy day tomorrow casserole
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients, then add to remaining ingredients.
Fold it all in and it will be thick and lumpy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or use your favorite icing.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Separate each biscuit and cut into 4 pieces. Mix pieces with sugar mixture until well coated.
Put pieces into a greased Bundt cake pan and set aside.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Simmer on low heat until completely melted.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake until biscuits rise.
Cool approximately 15 minutes before serving.

title: tomato florentine soup
directions: Prepare macaroni. Rinse and drain. Empty soup into large saucepan. Fill soup can with water and add to soup. Repeat. Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat. Add macaroni and simmer 15 minutes before serving.

title: pork chop and apple bake
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in shortening.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Arrange apples in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Arrange pork chops over apples.
Pour sherry over all. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in unpreheated oven.
Serves 6.

title: pa dutch filling(you call it "stuffing")
directions: Melt butter.
Add diced onions and celery.
Cook slowly until soft.
Cook potatoes to mash.
Break bread in pieces in large bowl, then add mashed potatoes, celery, onions and all butter. Add some milk.
Add eggs, more milk and seasonings.
Mix well and add more milk (like mashed potato consistency).
Bake in greased casserole 1/2 hour until brownish or put some in turkey or chicken.
Bake rest in dish.

title: cleo's slush
directions: Prepare orange juice using package directions.
Combine lemonade concentrate, orange juice, undrained maraschino cherries, vodka, brandy, rum, Squirt and undrained pineapple in large freezer container; mix well.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Place in punch bowl.
Garnish with peach slices, mandarin oranges or strawberries.

title: lemon supreme
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in the boiling water.
Let cool.
Beat eggs and add corn oil.
Mix in cake mix.
Beat well.
Add cool jello and pour into well-greased and bottom-lined angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven while cake is baking.
Remove from stove and leave in pan.
Mix 1 can lemonade concentrate with powdered sugar; pour over cake while it is hot. Let cool 1 hour or more.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients for a topping; pour over potatoes in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Combine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch well-greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites and salt.
Set aside.
In another mixer bowl, beat egg yolks, lime juice and condensed milk. Add 2 to 3 drops of green food coloring, if desired.
Fold into beaten egg whites and pour into graham cracker crust; bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat 1 cup heavy whipping cream until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Top pie and garnish with fresh lime slices and mint leaves.

title: penne with ham and pea cream sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add water and onions.
Cover for 7 minutes.
Then add garlic for 2 minutes.
Add heavy cream and ham; cook over low boil for 7 minutes.
Add marjoram, nutmeg, pepper and peas.
Mix slowly.
Add cooked pasta and Parmesan cheese and toss together.
Ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix herb stuffing with melted margarine and broth.
Place 1/2 mix in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix cooked chicken and onions. Spread over stuffing.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread over chicken and sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
May be kept in refrigerator overnight before baking.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: country sausage corn chowder
directions: Over medium-high heat, brown and crumble sausage in soup pot. While sausage begins to brown, add onions and red peppers, cook until tender and sausage is no longer pink.
Drain off excess dripping.
Add flour, stir well into mixture and cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Add milk and combine with sausage mixture.
Add cream corn and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes until base thickens.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the shortening and margarine; add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together 3 times.
Add to mixture alternately with milk which vanilla has been added to.
Blend thoroughly and put into a greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: broccoli, rice and ground beef casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and broccoli together.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza sticks
directions: Remove bread sticks from package and place in single layer on baking sheet(s). Top each with 5 slices of pepperoni and 1 tablespoon shredded cheese. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cooked through. Serve bread sticks with warm pizza sauce for dipping.

title: venison steak
directions: Cut
steak
into
serving
pieces.
Dredge
in
flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat bacon drippings or oil in a skillet and brown
meat.
Remove
meat; pour off excess fat. Stir 2 tablespoons flour into drippings.
When flour is brown, stir in enough milk to make gravy.	Dissolve soup mix in 1 cup water and add to
skillet.
Return
meat
to	pan.
Cover
and simmer 30 minutes over low heat.

title: roast
directions: Rub brown sugar into roast.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer and puncture meat.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Wrap very tightly in tinfoil and cook at 350° for about 3 hours or until tender. Add no water.
Can add black pepper.
Cook fat side down.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Soak raisins in hot water for 30 minutes.
Drain thoroughly. Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease 15 (1/2-cup) muffin pans. Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a bowl.
Stir in raisins, carrots, apple, almonds and coconut.
Beat eggs with oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture until just combined. Divide batter among muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown and tester inserted comes out clean, about 20 to 22 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: puppy chow cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and butter until smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal and mix well.
Pour powdered sugar over cereal.
Cover and shake mixture to coat. Repeat until well coated.
Kids love it.

title: rice - mexican-style
directions: In a large skillet, saute rice and garlic in oil until rice is golden, stirring often.
Add beef broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and boil 5 minutes.
Add onion, tomatoes, peas, parsley and salt.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook until rice is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Fluff before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk and roll in the flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Put butter in 9
x 2 inch baking dish and melt in 425° oven.	Put chicken in pan, skin side down, and bake 30 minutes.	Turn and bake 15 minutes more, or until tender.
Mix remaining buttermilk and soup together and pour around chicken.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: betty's millionaire pie(first prize winner)
directions: First
Layer:
Pour
melted
butter over flour and powdered sugar.
Mix together and add nuts.
Press into pie plate greased with oil.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and add the rest of ingredients.
Place in pie pan.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Serve whipped cream on top.

title: potatoes in cream
directions: In a large saucepan melt the butter then mix in the flour, salt and pepper to make a smooth paste.
Stir in the onion and cream.
Cook stirring until the mixture is smooth and thickened. Add the potatoes and continue to cook until the potatoes are heated through; sprinkle on the parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low calorie key lime pie
directions: Make Jell-O ahead per directions on box. After cooling and before it sets up, whip in Key lime yogurt, Jell-O and whip cream. Pour in pie crust and top with whipped cream.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, butter and morsels in microwave about 2 minutes.
Then pour over Rice Chex cereal and stir.
Then place mixture in a brown paper sack and add a box of powdered sugar, shaking well.
Store in airtight container.
Delicious snack and easy to do.

title: fruit juice cooler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a pitcher.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.

title: graham pralines
directions: Break graham crackers in half and place on cookie sheet.
Boil oleo, sugar and pecans for four minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and spread evenly.
Bake for 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool slightly and remove onto waxed paper.

title: cheesy (hash browns) potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, in two 8 x 8-inch pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese and
sugar.
Add fruit, nuts and marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix molasses with water. Add dry ingredients, alternately with water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat 5 minutes after each egg is added.
Pour into pie shell; chill until set.
Top with whipped topping; garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into 3 balls. Roll one ball in pepper, one in parsley and one in paprika, covering entire surfaces.
Serve with crackers.

title: savory venison stew
directions: Dust the meat with flour; brown in a skillet containing the bacon drippings.
Transfer both to a stew pot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer slowly for at least 2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: six-in-one casserole
directions: Layer in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish the potatoes, celery, pepper, onions and hamburger.
Pour tomatoes over top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: mama's christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar, juices, and enough water to make a gallon.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Combine 1/4 c. gravy with beef, bread cubes, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf; place in shallow baking pan.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine egg whites until stiff and add sugar, berries and lemon juice in large bowl; beat to stiff peaks. Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours.
Cut in 10 to 12 squares.

title: banana berry brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to a boil.
Mix the brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Pour into greased and floured pizza pan. Bake for 25 minutes.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Pour over crust and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Cool and top with fruit and drizzle with chocolate.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and let stand.
Cream the shortening and sugars together.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add the oatmeal and water mixture; beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon and set aside.
Brown ground beef.
Drain off drippings.
Add all ingredients, except bacon.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or for 10 minutes in microwave.
Crumble bacon on top past cooking.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 to 5 minutes. Take off heat. Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Drop onto wax paper with spoon while mixture is warm.
Let cool before serving.

title: miss willie's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove meat from bone.
Cut in small pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, mix and bring to a boil the chicken broth and soup.
In another bowl, combine melted margarine, pepper, flour and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly to form batter.
Pour broth mixture over chicken. Spread batter over top.
Bake at 425°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream chicken over toasted english muffins
directions: Brown onion in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Add soup and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken, peas and seasoning.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Toast English muffins.
For each serving, place muffin half on plate and place one slice of cheese on top of muffin.
Spoon hot creamed chicken over top of cheese.
Two fat grams per serving; 179 calories per serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat 3 eggs until light, then add sugar, vanilla and oil. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix egg mixture with flour mixture.
Add shredded zucchini and 1 cup nuts. Grease and flour pan.
Use 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork; bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then scoop out pulp.

title: onion soup
directions: In saucepan cook 1 large sliced onion in butter 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add beef broth and a dash of Worcestershire sauce and cook 5 minutes.
Divide soup between two ovenproof bowls.
Top each with toasted French bread and half the Swiss cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 2.

title: yams(candied)
directions: Boil yams until nearly done.
Let cool and slice.
Place in baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Pour over yams and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with pecans and broil about 5 minutes. "Watch closely."
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cooked lemon pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add lemon juice and rind.
Sprinkle in meal and flour.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 300° for about 45 minutes, or until done.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour in 1/2 eggs and 1/2 cheese and one can chilies, then repeat with the other half.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Can serve immediately or later reheat in microwave.

title: plain cake(50 years)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water in large bowl until Jell-O is dissolved. Add 7-Up. Put in the refrigerator until it starts to set. Add cream cheese, crushed pineapple, carrots, chopped nuts and Cool Whip. Mix well. Put in mold and chill until set.

title: koenigs berger klops(meatballs)
directions: Soak in milk to cover 1 slice bread about 1-inch thick.
Beat well 2 eggs and add to 1 1/2 lb. finely ground meat (1/2 lb. beef, 1/2 lb. veal, 1/2 lb. pork).
Melt 1 tablespoon butter, saute in it until golden 1/2 cup finely chopped onion.
Add them to the meat. Wring the milk from the bread and add the bread to the meat along with the above ingredients.
Combine well.
Do this literally with the hands.
Shape lightly into 2-inch balls.
Drop into 5 cups boiling stock (made with 4 bouillon cubes).
Simmer covered for about 15 minutes.
Remove meat balls from the stock.
Make gravy of it by using for every cup of stock 2 tablespoons butter, 2 tablespoons flour; correct the seasoning.
Cook and stir until smooth and hot.
Add 2 tablespoons capers, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 2 tablespoons chopped parsley.
Reheat the meatballs in the gravy.
Serve over boiled noodles or spaetzle (German egg dumplings).
Serves 6; makes about ten 2 inch balls.

title: banana puddingdallas, texas
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in milk and cook until slightly thickened, stir to keep from sticking. Beat eggs and combine a little hot mixture with eggs, then cook until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Crumble 1 tube (or less) Ritz crackers and put in butter where onions were sauteed.
Spread on top of ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 30 minutes).

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Separate the rolls into rectangles; seal the perforations.
Spoon chicken mixture onto center of each roll.
Fold the four corners to the center and seal.
Brush tops of rolls with melted margarine.
Dip in the croutons.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rotel (home canned)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large enamel pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into sterilized pints; seal and process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Combine beef and onion in electric skillet. Cook until browned. Drain.
Add pinto beans and remaining ingredients. Cover. Reduce heat. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: my favorite pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ginger, cinnamon, flour and sugar.
Beat egg whites lightly.
Add dry ingredients, then pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add milk; mix well.
Pour into two 10-inch pastry shells or 3 smaller shells. Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Beat Dream Whip and cold milk until nearly thick.
Add cream cheese; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
(If too stiff, add a little milk.)
Save 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Mix graham cracker crumbs in a bowl with 1 stick oleo, melted, and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press this in Pyrex pan.
Add Dream Whip, then the cherry pie filling, then some Dream Whip.
Top with some of the graham cracker crumbs.
Chill at least 24 hours.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries; heat for dissolving jello (do not use water).
Add the Coca-Cola to this mixture; let congeal slightly.
Break up cream cheese in food processor.
Add broken up cream cheese, pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Pour into individual molds or one large mold and let congeal.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: red cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage.
Remove outer leaves and core.
Shred very fine in a heavy saucepan or kettle.
Melt the butter with sugar.
Mix in shredded cabbage, grated apple, jelly and vinegar.
Blend thoroughly.
Simmer and stir 10 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water at a time and let it evaporate each time.
Cook and stir frequently for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt margarine, adding onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add spices and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve on hot rice.

title: betty's salsa(hot but good)
directions: Serve with cold poached salmon or other fish.

title: tracie's vegetable soup
directions: Combine water, lemon juice, basil, pepper, bouillon cubes, bay leaves and onion in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about an hour.
Stir in tomatoes and vegetables.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle soup with spinach or kale and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
You may also add cooked rice, potatoes or pasta to make this soup a meal.

title: sassy meat loaf
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl mix ground beef, oats, crackers, egg and soup mix.
Add milk if needed to make mixture moist.
Place mixture in a 9x9 baking dish.
Put cheese slices on top then pour tomato sauce over cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes or until center is browned.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: plum good cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a tube pan which has been greased and floured for 1 hour at 350°.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer vegetables as listed.
Spread mayonnaise on top, sealing completely.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Do not stir.
Chill overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Debone chicken and save broth.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until tender.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 stick oleo.
Add cheese, Ro-Tel and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup milk or more, if needed.
Combine all.
It is ready to eat!
Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: sausage egg bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cubed bread in bottom.
Top with cheese.
Brown and drain sausage.
Place on top of cheese. Beat eggs with milk and mustard and pour over.
Refrigerate overnight.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or more.

title: banana boats
directions: Peel back a long strip of banana peel on the inside curve, leaving end attached to banana.
Scoop out some banana; fill with marshmallow, chocolate and raisins (if desired).
Replace strip of peeling.
Wrap in foil.
Bake in embers 15 to 20 minutes, until banana and toppings are melted and blended.
Turn during baking.

title: shredded yams(serving size: 12)
directions: Shred yams into a gallon of ice water with 1 tablespoon salt. Soak for a few minutes.
Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it forms a light syrup.
Drain yams well.
Place yams in a buttered 12 x 9 x 3-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour juice over yams, then the syrup.
Dot the top with 4 tablespoons butter or margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until yams are translucent.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Cut meat diagonally across grain in strips 1/4-inch wide.
Brown quickly in butter.
Push meat to one side. Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook just until tender.
Add broth.
Heat to boiling.
Blend sour cream and flour.
Stir into broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Season to taste.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: strawberry summer delight
directions: Prepare jello according to package and let jell.
Add one cup strawberries to jello and add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Crumble angel food cake into mixture, holding back 1 cup for top.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and 1 cup strawberries on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining cake, crumbled finely, on top of strawberries.
Cool until firm.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cream shortening and sugar. Add vanilla and eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Add cocoa and mix thoroughly. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in sifted dry ingredients; add nuts. Spread mixture in pan. (Nuts may be added to top, optional.) Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: sesame cookies
directions: In one bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine wet ingredients.
Add wet ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and then milk.
Mix dry ingredients together in separate bowl.
Stir into the butter mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll dough and cut cookies.
Bake at 375° until edges are slightly browned, about 8 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl. Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breast on waxed paper.
Flatten to 1/4 inch thickness by using mallet or rolling pin.
Place one slice ham and one slice of Swiss cheese in center of each chicken breast. Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden picks.
Dip each chicken breast into beaten egg; coat well with bread crumbs.
Set aside.
Melt butter in heavy skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Place chicken in 12 x 8 x 2-inch ovenproof baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream, sherry and sliced mushrooms to drippings and stir together well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: soup delight
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until tender; drain water. Fry hamburger meat and drain. Add together and simmer 20 minutes; serve hot.

title: instant cappuccino
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
To serve, put 2 Tbsp. mix in cup and fill with boiling water.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg or shaved chocolate.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs in a bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet. Press 3 to 4 extra M&M's in each cookie.
Bake until light brown for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and flavoring together.
Add eggs, one at a time.

title: chartreuse of rice
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water.
Drain and line a greased mold or casserole about 1/2 inch deep.
Cut meat in fine pieces. Mix beaten egg with meat.
Add stock to meat and egg.
Fill center of mold with meat mixture.
Cover top of mold with remaining rice. Steam 30 minutes.
Turn from mold.
Serve hot with tomato sauce.

title: one vanilla milkshake
directions: Whirl all ingredients together in blender.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter 10 to 20 minutes.
Put oven on 350° (preheat).
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick southern burgers
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain.
Add soup, mustard and ketchup; mix.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve on buns topped with cheese. Toast in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Stir Bisquick, milk, sugar and butter until soft dough forms. Drop by 6 spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and eggs.
Add sugars and dry ingredients.
Mix in flour last.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In saucepan cook onions in butter until tender.
Add bouillon, pepper, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer covered for 20 to 25 minutes to blend flavors.

title: fried chicken
directions: Put floured chicken in cold grease and turn up on high.
Only turn the chicken once (or twice if necessary).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat butter and stir in flour.
Combine milk and broth; stir into flour mixture.
Cook, stirring until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Blend in salt, pepper, nutmeg and cheese.
After cheese melts, remove from heat.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes.
Mix half the sauce with spaghetti and mushrooms.
Place in large baking dish.
Mix remaining sauce with chicken and place on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: hershey's cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Pour syrup into mixture; mix until smooth.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes in oblong pan. Prepare icing 5 minutes before cake is done; pour hot icing over hot cake.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done through.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: cindy's chili
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook for approximately 1 hour.
If you want noodles, add boiled macaroni or spaghetti.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat the eggs.
Add Karo, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add pecans and mix well again.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Do not prick pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced tea - hot or cold
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water and 8 teaspoons per quart of water.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Boil potatoes until done. Drain and let cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream together.
Beat potatoes into cream cheese mixture. Add margarine, garlic salt and chives.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into dish. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Cook butter, sugar, salt until sugar is melted.
Mix in half the almonds and cook to hard crack stage (about 300 degrees F). Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Cool.
Melt the milk chocolate morsels and spread half of mixture over candy.
Sprinkle half the remaining almonds.
Turn onto wax paper and repeat.

title: salsa verde (green salsa)
directions: Boil (over medium-high heat) first 4 ingredients in 3 cups of water until tomatillos come apart. Place green onions, lime juice and cilantro in blender and pour in warm tomatillo mixture. Blend until smooth (about 60 seconds); cover lid with a cloth and hold the lid down before and during the blending process since the contents are hot and are likely to "explode" all over the kitchen. Add additional salt to taste if needed.

title: pizza delight
directions: Tired of being the helpless man?
Now you can take charge. It's really not that hard to fix dinner.
(Yell at kids.)
Look up the number for local Pizza Hut.
They're in white pages under "P." Using index finger of right hand, call Pizza Hut.
(Yell at kids.) Tell them you have a coupon.
Order 1 large pizza, hand tossed, 1/2 sausage, 1/2 pepperoni.
Note time.
(Yell at kids.)

title: sausage and macaroni
directions: Combine all ingredients in a lightly greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour in moderate oven (350°).

title: orange julius
directions: Blend together in blender.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: forgotten souffle
directions: *May use 1 pound bacon, crisply cooked and broken, or more.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash until tender; season.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook into a casserole dish until onions are cooked or begins to brown.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except cabbage leaves.
Form mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Wrap cabbage leaves around balls and secure with toothpicks.
Place rolls in Dutch oven; cover with water.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Saute onions and peppers in a skillet with a little oil. Place in a crock-pot.
Brown steak in skillet and place in crock-pot.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar, mushrooms, parsley flakes, salt and pepper together.
Pour over steak.
Stir.
Let simmer 2 to 3 hours or until done.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in chopped walnuts.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine all and pour over crackers, coating well. Warm in 250° oven for 15 minutes, turn off and leave for 15 more minutes.

title: chicken broccoli curry
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Cook in boiling water until still firm.
Drain.
Put broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Trim and cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Heat Teflon pan on high for 5 minutes. Saute chicken until opaque white.
Cook half of the chicken at a time.
Layer cooked chicken on top of broccoli.
In a bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Spread on top of the chicken. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes and serve with rice.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Stir in Rice Krispies, oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: quick yeast rolls (1 hour rolls)
directions: Heat milk and shortening together until shortening melts.
Add crumbled yeast cake and flour.
Place mixture in greased bowl for 30 minutes.
Shape pieces of dough the size of a large egg in a round ball.
Flatten with hand into an oblong shape.
Place piece of butter in the middle.
Fold over until edges almost meet for Parker House rolls.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: christmas morning breakfast casserole
directions: In a large greased casserole dish, layer bread cubes, cheese, mushrooms and bacon.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour layered mixture. Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in large airtight bowl.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar together and pour over vegetables.
Stir well and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
This keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: spanish corn
directions: Combine corn, tomatoes, onion, sugar, salt and pepper in a casserole dish.
Top with browned crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: cornish hens with sauterne sauce, pearl onions and spinach(for 4 people)
directions: Heat honey; add non-alcoholic Sauterne and stock.
Boil for 20 minutes, until reduced.
Add soy sauce and cook for 3 minutes. Whisk with 2 tablespoons butter, 1 at a time at room temperature.

title: ham and cheese bake
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut slices in half.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Take half the bread and line bottom of pan. Layer ham and cheeses.
Cover with remaining bread slices. Combine eggs, milk, onion salt and dried mustard.
Slowly pour the mixture over the bread, meat and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry yogurt shake
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Blend at high speed for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Makes 5 servings.

title: plum bread
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar, eggs and baby food.
In separate bowl mix dry ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Stir together by hand.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or use 2 1/4 x 4-inch tea loaf pans.
Bake for 22 minutes.

title: snow people cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat margarine and cream cheese on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 the flour and all the sugar, baking powder, egg, vanilla and almond extract; beat well.
Beat or stir in remaining flour until combined.

title: ginger carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in sugar; cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Add Cool Whip. Beat until creamy.

title: chicken bola gai
directions: Mix dry
ingredients
and coat chicken pieces and brown in 4 tablespoons
of
margarine.
Combine
1 cup of pineapple syrup, from Number
can of pineapple slices, and 1/2 cup of soy sauce. Place
fried chicken in shallow casserole and pour pineapple sauce
over
them.
Cover casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Baste
to 3 times.
Use pineapple slices for side dish salad.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Combine bacon, cheese and onion; put in bottom of pie plate. Blend remaining ingredients together for 1 minute and pour on top of bacon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package.
Brown and drain hamburger. Add pepper, cut in strips. Cut onion into rings and add.
Add Prego sauce.
Heat until hot.
Pour over spaghetti. Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice the apples and place in an 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix together in a small bowl the margarine, 1 cup sugar, egg and flour.
Pour over apple slices.
Sprinkle with the nutmeats, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy. Beat egg into creamed mixture. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix
into creamed mixture until just blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes. Remove to foil on countertop.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Brown onion in margarine. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl, then pour into pan or dish and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soups and enchilada sauce.
Layer in a casserole dish: crushed Doritos, chicken, soups and cheese.
You may make several layers.
Heat for about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour a 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until very light and fluffy.
At low speed, add chocolate, beating just until blended.
Beat in flour mixture (in fourths), alternately with milk (in thirds), beginning and ending with flour mixture; beat just until combined.
Pour batter into prepared pan; bake 60 to 65 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Then turn out on rack; cool completely.
To serve, cut thinly into 16 slices.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash unpeeled potatoes and cut lengthwise into 4 wedges. Place in baking dish, skin side down.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours. Brush with oil and cheese occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers and 1 cup of vinegar in blender.
