Run until small flakes of peppers.
Mix sugar and 1 cup of vinegar in a large boiler.
Add peppers to this mixture.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Skim and put into 1/2 pint jars. Seal with lids or paraffin wax.
This makes 7 or 8 jars.

title: barbecue meat
directions: Cook meat, salt and pepper together until tender.
Cooking overnight in a crock-pot is best.
Mix all other ingredients together and cook until onion and pepper it tender.
Add this to meat.

title: ruth's roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on tortilla shells (8 shells).
Roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: french apple cobbler
directions: To make filling, combine apples, 3/4 c. sugar, 2 Tbsp. flour, cinnamon, 1/4 tsp. salt, vanilla, and 1/2 c. water in a medium bowl.
Put in a 9 inch x 9 inch baking pan.
Dot with butter.

title: acini de pepe fruit salad dessert
directions: Cook pasta in salted water for 12 minutes; rinse in cold water.
Drain.
Drain the canned fruit.
Put the juice in a saucepan and add the eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over drained pasta and let chill several hours or overnight

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Great on cheese toast or crackers.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Slice berries in 3 or 4 slices. Grate rind of orange to use in bread and squeeze out juice.
Put juice in a cup with the oil and add enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup of liquid.
Combine with dry ingredients and beaten egg. Add cranberries and nuts, put in greased and floured loaf pan and bake for about 1 hour in 325° oven.
When cool, put in refrigerator wrapped in foil until ready to serve.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix meat and eggs.
Add bread crumbs until most moisture is absorbed.
Shape balls (2 inches).
Brown in olive oil.
Simmer in tomato sauce of choice (2 hours).

title: beryl's pineapple carrot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; let cool.
Add pineapple.
When it begins to set, mix whipped cream with sugar and mayonnaise. Stir in carrots.
Add this mixture to Jell-O and chill until firm.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix.
Roll into balls, then roll in sugar.
Do not press down. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: On large cookie sheet, pat down a layer of crescent rolls. Press the seams together so the cookie sheet is covered.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Spread mixture of the next 3 ingredients on pastry.
Cover with vegetables and cheese.

title: wild rice mushroom soup
directions: Melt oleo in large saucepan over medium heat; cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup of chicken broth and flour; blend until smooth.
Stir flour mixture and remaining broth into mushroom mixture.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and stir in tomato paste until well blended.
Add milk and rice; mix well.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sherry; sprinkle with parsley.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly. Add the mayonnaise. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine oleo, water and chocolate in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in combined flour and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and salt; mix well. Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter several times for marble effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients.
Toss with fork.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: quick nut coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and spices in a bowl. Cut in shortening with a fork or pastry blender until mixture is like coarse crumbs. Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture for top of coffee cake. To rest of crumb mixture, add well beaten eggs and coffee. Mix lightly. Pour into well-greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle top of cake with remaining crumb mixture and the chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pear waldorf salad
directions: Toss all ingredients. Serve on salad greens. Serves 4.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and keep in a jar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan for 45 minutes.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Grease a large baking dish and line bottom with dried beef. Place chicken on top of beef. Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together.
Pour mixture over chicken and sprinkle with paprika. Do not add salt as the beef is salty!
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Divide cocktail peanuts.
Melt butterscotch on medium heat in double boiler.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Stir up and spoon out on wax paper and cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables for 20 minutes.
Add milk to flour; stir until well blended.
Add milk to vegetables; cook until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into walnut-sized balls and freeze on a cookie sheet.
When frozen, transfer to a freezer container and store until needed in your freezer.
Remove as many as needed and return the rest to the freezer.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: alice's potato soup with dumplings
directions: Cook
celery in 2 cups water 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, onion and
cups
water.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes. Add butter
and seasoning.
Mix egg with Bisquick.
Mix well. Add enough
milk
to
make a stiff batter.
Add 1 cup milk to soup. Bring
to
boil.
Drop
batter by teaspoonfuls in soup. Cook 5 minutes.
Put
lid	on
tilted or soup will boil over. Cook 10
to 12 minutes.
Take dumplings out and put on a plate so they will not get sad.
Use a 4 or 5 quart cookpot.

title: kentucky corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine with beaten eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix well to blend the mix with the canned corns. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil and vinegar, together.
Mix oil and vinegar together and toss with salad.

title: pineapple crunch cake
directions: Cream white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add pineapple.
Sift and add flour, salt and soda.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: steak diane
directions: Trim steaks of all fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper on both sides.
Put 3 tablespoons of butter in large skillet or wok.
Heat until foam begins to subside.
Cook 2 to 3 steaks one minute on each side; remove.
Repeat with other steaks.
Melt rest of butter or margarine in pan.
Add green onion; cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Add dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Return steaks to pan.
Cook one minute on each side.
Transfer to warm platter or serving plates.
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice to sauce remaining in pan.
Add 2 tablespoons chopped parsley and 1 tablespoon finely chopped chives.
Heat through.
Pour over steaks. Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Note:
If you like, you can use onion soup instead of mushroom and you can add 1 (6 ounce) can water chestnuts, drained and sliced and 1/2 cup of chopped parsley.

title: lisa's crab fondue
directions: Melt all together until smooth, then add crab meat.
Serve with French bread (cubed large).
Very rich.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Frost with mayonnaise.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Place in baking dish. Melt oleo in saucepan, stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thick.
Add cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.
Stir.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy chicken fingers
directions: Combine chicken and milk. Set aside.
Combine masa harina and next 7 ingredients. Combine flour and black pepper in a separate bowl.
To coat chicken, dip milk soaked pieces first in flour, back in milk and then in masa harina mixture.
Place on wax paper. Freeze for at least 4 hours.
Place frozen chicken fingers on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crisp.
Serve chicken fingers with creamy green salsa.
Yields 8 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs, flour, salt, pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend the soup and mayonnaise; spread over the chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover with stuffing.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake 30 to 40 more minutes at 350°.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: Make layers from your favorite layer cake recipe or use one box yellow cake mix using directions on box.

title: stir and drop cookie
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add flour and flavoring. Drop on cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen cookies.
This is a very light cookie.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Spread chicken and veggies in dish.
In separate bowl, mix soup, milk and butter. Stir until smooth.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 400° 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter (beat until smooth); gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in lemon extract.
Add flour to the creamed mixture, beating well until smooth.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Combine together soup, onion, milk, salt and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 soup mixture and 1/2 sausage.
Repeat again, ending with sausage.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender. Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted, 2 to 3 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake at 375°.
Cool. Hang upside down to cool for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook scallions in margarine with eggs.
After eggs are firm, add rice and soy sauce.
Cook until hot.
Can add cooked chicken, pork or beef.
Serves 4.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Add tomato sauce and taco mix; heat together 10 minutes.
Put chips in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Spoon meat over chips.
Top with cheese; heat until melted.

title: peanut butter balls(buckeyes)
directions: Mix together peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine. Form small balls by rolling a small amount in palm of hands.
(If sticky, put a little powdered sugar on your hands.)
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin, if desired.
Dip balls, one at a time, then place on wax paper to cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer until warm, then add cheese.

title: unbelievable lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in blender except coconut.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: honey crisps
directions: Combine oats, coconut and flour in bowl.
Combine brown sugar, butter and honey in saucepan; bring to boil, stirring constantly. Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients; stir until blended.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool; store in tightly covered container.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: nestle butterscotch morsels
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon with milk.
Stir in oats, morsels, raisins and nuts. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bring the butter, water and shortening to boil, then let cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add to first mixture.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili-bean bake
directions: Pour hominy into large casserole dish.
Spread chili beans on top of hominy.
Sprinkle shredded cheese as topping.
(Crushed Fritos may be sprinkled over cheese.)
Bake in oven or microwave oven until thoroughly hot and cheese is melted.

title: red beans and rice with  ham
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water, 2-inches above beans.
Let soak 8 hours.
Drain.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Then bake in oven for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon and orange jello
directions: Prepare each as directed on package.
Then mix together and refrigerate until set.
When set, spread on Cool Whip and serve!

title: cheese soup
directions: Grate cheese very fine so it will melt easily.
Melt butter over low heat; saute' vegetables.
Add broth, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add soup (undiluted), cheese, parsley, tabasco, salt & pepper.
Stir in sour cream; simmer (do not boil) for 15 minutes. Add Sherry to your taste and stir.
Yield - 10 cups.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Make Whole Wheat Pizza Crust (or any other).
Spoon ham over crust (drain first).
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
(At this point, you can cover with plastic wrap, not foil, and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Add 5 minutes to cooking time.)
In a medium bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour onto crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place rice in casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup mixed with the milk and pour over rice.
Place skinless chicken breasts (cut in smaller pieces, if desired) on top of rice.
Sprinkle with seasoning mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake approximately 15 minutes.

title: turkey hash
directions: In a 5 quart saucepan, saute onions and celery in margarine 2 to 3 minutes over medium-high heat until tender.
Add broth, potatoes, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Once mixture starts to simmer, cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in turkey.
In a bowl, gradually add milk to cornstarch.
Stir into soup.
Cook on medium heat until soup thickens.

title: animal crackers
directions: Grind 1/2 cup oatmeal in blender until fine.
Add honey, salt, flour, baking soda, margarine and buttermilk.
Roll very thin; cut with animal cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Soften for 10 minutes.
Add cottage cheese that has been warmed.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Stir down.
Divide into 2 loaves.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in pan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Take off heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over cornflakes.
Make into cookies on aluminum foil.

title: quick open faced sandwich
directions: For each sandwich(es) layer in order given.
Set sandwich under broiler.
Cook just until tomato is hot and cheese starts to melt. Good quick meal!

title: ritz cracker snacks
directions: Cook dates and milk over medium heat for 10 minutes or until thick.
Stir in nuts.
Let cool for 2 minutes.
Spread on crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: moussaka(eggplant casserole)
directions: Slice eggplant 1/4 inch thick.
Lightly coat with flour and brown in large skillet with 6 tablespoons oil.
Drain eggplant. Saute chopped onions until tender, then add meat.
Saute 5 minutes or until done.
Blend in parsley, paprika and salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato saue and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Set aside for a couple hours to let flavors blend.
Refrigerate.

title: pina colada dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and rum until smooth.
Fold in 4 cups of Cool Whip, crushed pineapple with juice and 1 1/3 cans of coconut.
Spread into large rectangular glass baking dish.
Freeze several hours.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Garnish with cherries and pineapple slices.
Freeze. Allow to sit out 10 to 12 minutes prior to slicing.
Makes 15 to 16 servings.
Can be halved and made in pie plate.
This can be made several days ahead and keep frozen.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In long dish melt margarine; add self-rising flour and chopped nuts.
Press out in bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; cool!
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over cooled crust.
Mix small package instant chocolate pudding and milk.
Mix until pudding begins to thicken.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread the rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: brownie meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed on box except stir nuts into dough.
Bake as directed; cool.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch, water, Karo and vanilla.
Bring to boil and cook until thick and clear.
Remove from stove.
Add jello.
Arrange strawberries for each pie and pour hot mixture over top.
Chill and top with whipped cream. Makes 2 pies.

title: leftover soup(betty than it sounds)
directions: Whenever you have leftover vegetables (raw or cooked), put them into a large container in your freezer.
Make sure they are covered with liquid (the juice from the vegetables or plain water) or they'll suffer freezer burn.
Date the container so it won't stay in the freezer too long!
When you're ready to make your soup, thaw and heat your vegetables.
Add canned tomatoes, chopped with juice until it's soupy!

title: jim's pot of beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight. Pour soak water off. Rinse. Add water to about an inch above beans. Bring to a boil. Lower heat to simmer. Add chili powder, onion flakes, garlic powder, Woodies cooking sauce, red pepper and black pepper. Add boiling water as needed while cooking. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add bouillon cubes 20 to 30 minutes before done.

title: italian delight(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Fry onion, garlic and ground beef until brown. Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 55 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, bacon and raisins in large bowl. Store in closed container for 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli on bottom of baking dish. Mix cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise and spread over chicken. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top; sprinkle with bread crumbs. Drizzle melted margarine over bread crumbs.

title: banana breakfast drink
directions: Combine yogurt, banana, milk, honey, orange juice and ice in blender until smooth.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses. Garnish with an orange and banana slice.
Yield: 2 cups.
Serves 4 when doubled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	10 minutes;
cool and drain thoroughly. Combine
all ingredients, except crumbs and margarine.
Grease a casserole
dish;
pour in combined ingredients and top with cracker crumbs melted in margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
May
need to cover with foil if crumbs get too brown on top.

title: crisscross peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix white and brown sugar; cream with shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, then add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Roll in your hands the dough in the size of a walnut.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Press with fork (dipped in water) to form crisscross.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen cookies.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Flour the walnuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift together remaining flour, salt and baking powder.
Add this alternately with milk to the butter-sugar-egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in walnuts. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom and up sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan (cut slices for sides).
Combine milk and eggs.
Beat.
Pour over bread.
Put meat and cheese mix on top; push bread into mixture to saturate.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove cover and push bread into mixture again before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 5 to 8 adults.

title: glazed cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Line cupcake tins with 2 papers each.
Put one vanilla wafer in each tin.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with pie filling and chill at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownie chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in xxxx sugar, vanilla and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir in more water until spreading consistency.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream the first 2 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add next 2 ingredients gradually.
Blend well.
Add fruit cocktail.
May add chopped nuts, if desired.
Beat well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: brown betty
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put the dough in a buttered deep oblong pan or square 12 x 12-inch, then very carefully put the hot syrup over it a spoonful at a time.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Add pie filling and spread in an even layer.
Sprinkle dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Place butter in pats over top, covering completely.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until top is golden.
Serve warm or cooled.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Combine margarine, oil, baking cocoa and milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Add flour and sugar; mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread frosting over cake.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Chill.
Shake well before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Set oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine chicken, mayo, onion, celery, lemon juice, almonds, soup and 1 cup shredded cheese. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (greased).
Sprinkle chips, the rest of the cheese and garnish with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
Serves approximately 8 to 10 per pound.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Coat cereal mixture. Put in grocery bag with powdered sugar and shake.

title: mama's banana cake
directions: Mix sugar
and
shortening.
Add
eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking
soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, bananas and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pans 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dressing for fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook until thick, let cool. Beat 1 cup cream. Add to dressing. Pour over fruit of choice. Let stand 2 hours.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Mix in saucepan:
butter, cocoa, oil and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour first, then sugar.
Mix. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° on greased and floured large cookie sheet for 20 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Jell until shaky and marshmallows are melted.
Fold in small carton of Cool Whip.
Add 1 can drained chunked pineapple.

title: congealed cheese salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in dish and refrigerate until it sets up.
When it has set, remove and stir well.
Transfer to another bowl.
Stirring it makes it look different from a congealed salad.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine margarine with remaining ingredients and return to baking pan in which margarine was melted.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
This will be pretty moist in center.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Finely chop green onions and corned beef.
Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Best if chilled before serving.

title: oven vegetables
directions: Melt the butter and add the seasoning mix.
Bake the vegetables in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Pour the butter spoon by spoon every 10 minutes.
Bake for 20 minutes at 450°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° to 350° in three loaf pans. Wrap, while warm, in aluminum foil.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.

title: no fat boiled custard
directions: Mix eagle brand milk and pudding, then add skim milk. Chill 1 hour.

title: herbed cheese & cracker bits
directions: Place the crackers in a large freezer container.
In a bowl, mix the oil, salad dressing mix, dill, garlic powder, and celery salt.
Pour this mixture over the crackers, and cover.
Invert it to coat the crackers with seasoning.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours, turning the container ever so often to keep crackers coated. Let the mixture come to room temperature before serving.
Store in container in refrigerator.

title: chicken with asparagus
directions: Pour oil in pan at medium heat.
Add chicken and saute slowly (6 minutes) or until white and opaque.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Cook asparagus as directed.
Drain and place in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Place chicken pieces on asparagus and pour soup mixture over it.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown meat and then drain.
Add onions and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add tomato paste and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix well. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in a 9-inch pie pan, pressing together to form a crust.
Flute edge.
Fill with meat mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy caramels
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil and butter the foil; set aside.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil slowly for 4 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook until candy thermometer reads 238°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Cool.
Remove from pan and cut into 1-inch squares.
Wrap each in wax paper.
Yield:
64 pieces.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend
together
flour, brown sugar, crushed Ritz, soda and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add
coconut
and	vanilla;
stir	to
blend. Press half the
mixture
into	an
8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover
mixture with cherry pie filling and top with remaining crumb
mixture. Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: peach crisp
directions: Slice and pit peaches; spread into a large baking dish.
Put over top of peaches 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons water.
In a bowl, put Bisquick, cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
In a separate small bowl, beat egg.
Mix egg into Bisquick mix and toss around until crumbly.
Pour that over top of peaches and pour melted butter over that.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses circles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add molasses.
Beat well.
Combine vinegar and milk (or cream).
Sift flour, spices, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk mix.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped pork chops
directions: Wrap each chop with a slice of bacon, securing with a toothpick.
Place chops in a 2-quart shallow casserole dish in a single layer.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops. Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn once and remove cover after 40 minutes.

title: smoked bluefish
directions: Combine brine ingredients. Soak fillets overnight in a glass or ceramic dish in brine.
After soaking in brine, wash fillets thoroughly and pat dry before smoking.

title: vegetable snacks
directions: Cut cucumbers into nice circular shapes and spread with salt. Wait a minute or two and serve.

title: egg white crust
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until foamy. Add sugar gradually, beating until very stiff peaks hold.
Fold in finely chopped pecans and vanilla.
Spread in 8-inch pie tin; build up sides 1/2-inch.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Delicious for frozen strawberry pie or any icebox pies.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Cook chicken in skillet in oil until no longer pink.
Drain and add all other ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve in tortilla shells or taco shells.
Good with rice as a side dish.
This is a great Girl Scout campfire recipe.

title: festive marshmallow roll
directions: Melt chips and butter over low heat, stirring to combine. Remove from heat and blend in eggs; stir in powdered sugar.
Add marshmallows and nuts, blending well.
Shape into 2 or 3 rolls on wax paper to which coconut has been sprinkled.
Roll in coconut as they are shaped.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill.
Slice (approximately 1/4-inch thickness).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Sprinkle potato chips over top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened margarine.
Stir in nuts and Nestle Toll House semi-sweet morsels.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cover diced apples with sugar.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes. Beat eggs, oil and vanilla together.
Mix apple and egg mixtures together.
Mix flour, soda, salt and pecans.
Grease pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: party crackers
directions: Mix dressing, oil, dill and lemon pepper in a small bowl. Pour mixture over oyster crackers and stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Goes great with seafood gumbo.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Boil onions, celery and carrot strips for 7 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole; cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all juices from vegetables.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend well and enjoy.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind coarse tomatoes, peppers and onions. Put together in large pan; put the salt in and let stand 10 minutes. Drain, then mix all the spices, sugar and vinegar in it. Boil 10 minutes. Put hot in jars and seal.

title: dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir together all ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Swirl in 1/4 cup grated cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry chiffon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese.
Whip together until smooth.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, strawberries and nuts.
Whip well chilled evaporated milk.
Fold into jello mixture and pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: judy's brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa and nuts.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°. Great with frosting on top.

title: apple drop cookies
directions: In large bowl mix butter, sugars and egg.
Mix well, then add soda, cinnamon, salt, cloves, nutmeg and milk.
Mix well, then add flour.
Mix and add apples.
Can add raisins if desired.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add beaten egg.
Add salt and milk.
Dough should be sticky.
Pinch off a bit and knead with flour; roll out, cut into pieces and drop into boiling broth.
Do not stir.
Punch dumplings into broth with spoon.

title: ham delights
directions: Cut through middle of rolls.
Cream margarine; add poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Spread top and bottom with mixture.
Add one layer of ham and top with one layer of cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut up individually.
Makes 60.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine last three ingredients for dressing.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream the butter.
Beat in the sugar and eggs.
Stir in potatoes, milk and dry ingredients. Additional flour can be added if mixture is too soft to handle. Roll on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out and drop into hot fat in deep fryer.
The fat should be hot enough to brown a cube of bread in one minute, or 370° by a fat thermometer.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Stir in enough milk to form a soft dough onto well floured board; knead gently about 10 times.
Form dough into 12 small balls.
Flatten and place side by side in Redi-Pan round cake pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve hot with butter. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon together. Put 1/3 of this mixture in bottom of pie shell. Fill the pie shell with sliced apples. Sprinkle the remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture over the apples. Mix the other 1/2 cup sugar, flour and margarine until mixture is crumbly. Pile on top of the sliced apples. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes. If you wish to freeze the pie, freeze before baking.

title: hen and dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and put meat and stock from hen to moisten ingredients.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: lazy man's biscuits
directions: Mix well and drop in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: spicy mustard chicken
directions: Combine mustard and apple juice; shake well.
Remove skin from chicken breasts and brown in a nonstick skillet.
Slice onion on top of the chicken breasts.
Pour mustard and apple juice mixture over breasts and onion.
Cover and cook until sauce is slightly thick.
If mustard and apple juice do not cover chicken, add more sauce.

title: fumi salad
directions: Chop cabbage and green onion tops.
Combine.
Broil sesame seed and sliced almonds (until golden).
Add to cabbage and onion. Combine rice vinegar, salt, sugar and oil.
Mix into other ingredients.

title: sweet spiced zuc pickles
directions: Combine sliced zucchini and onions in a large glass bowl and soak 1 hour with enough cold water to cover. Rinse and drain. Combine remaining ingredients.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 5 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers 1/2 inch thick, soak in pickling lime and cold water.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Makes nice gifts.

title: honey pecan biscuits
directions: Blend honey and cinnamon. Divide mixture among greased muffin cups.
Put 3 pecan halves in each cup.
Place one biscuit in each cup. Bake according to biscuit label directions.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each. Add sour cream and beat well. Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda, plus 2 teaspoons almond flavoring or 1 each almond and vanilla.
Flour board with 1/2 flour and 1/2 powdered sugar, enough for the dough to handle easily.
Roll out dough about 1/4-inch thick, then dip cookie cutters in powdered sugar and cut as desired. Bake at 350° to 375° until slightly browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over cut vegetables.
Always cover with clear wrap, no plastic lids.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix beans, taco seasoning and chilies.
Pour into 12-inch serving platter.
In separate bowl, mash avocados and add lemon juice and 1/2 jar taco sauce and mix.
Spread avocado mixture over beans.
Next layer sour cream over avocado mixture.
Spread chopped lettuce over sour cream, add grated cheese, black olives and last 1/2 jar taco sauce on top.
Serve with lots of corn chips.

title: noodle pudding(serves 6 to 8.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour in greased 9 x 9-inch or 6 cup ring mold.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in pan.
Press 1/4 cup brown sugar into melted butter.
Press pecans into pan and set aside.

title: overnight caramel french toast
directions: In a small saucepan, combine corn syrup, oleo and brown sugar.
Simmer until syrupy.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan. Lay slices of bread over syrup.
Beat eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Uncover pan and bake for 45 minutes. Serve hot--can be reheated.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil to soft ball stage.
Add soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pour in pie filling.
Next, add can of pineapple with juice.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over this. Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts if desired and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Must dip not slice.

title: deluxe peas and celery
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add celery, mushrooms, pimento, onion, salt, savory and pepper.
Saute, uncovered, stirring frequently for about 7 minutes.
Add cooked peas and heat until hot.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cook pork chops until done.
Pinch into bite size pieces. Place in casserole dish.
Pinch canned biscuits into bite size pieces.
Beat egg and soup; pour over chops and biscuits.
Bake at 425° until biscuits are done.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Combine beef, potatoes, onions, eggs, barbecue sauce, salt and pepper; mix well.
Press into casserole.
Place cheese on top and pour catsup over cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix the cake mix with the oil, eggs and water.
Crush 6 Oreos and put them into the cake mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip and add remaining crushed Oreos.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill. If dressing is too thick, simply thin it with a little milk or water.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients and add water and lemon juice.
Cook until thick. Peel apples and core and slice. Pack apples in quart jars. Cover with sugar liquid.
Boil water bath for 20 minutes.
Yields 7 quarts.

title: rigatoni with cream and sausage(rigatoni panna e salsicce)
directions: Cook macaroni per directions (al dente).
In the meantime, saute onion in 2/3 of the butter.
Do not let onion brown too much.
Add milk from time to time to prevent this.
When onion is well cooked, add sausage.
Add a little milk to keep from sticking; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Drain rigatoni.
Add remaining butter.
Add sausage mixture.
Follow with cream and cheese.
Add pepper per taste.
The mixing should be done quickly.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat meat in flour.
Brown meat in oil in large skillet.
Add gravy mix, soy sauce, mushrooms and liquid from chow mein vegetables.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add celery, onion and chow mein vegetables.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer until vegetables are tender.
Pour into shallow casserole; arrange noodles around edge.
Serve.

title: cherry streusel bars
directions: Beat softened butter; add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs all at once; beat until creamy.
Add flour and juice.
Beat for approximately 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pan.
Score batter into squares and spoon 1 tablespoon pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. While warm, drizzle glaze on top of squares.

title: luau salad
directions: Let vegetables marinate for 1 hour.
Add rice and mix well.

title: seafood pasta(great dish - easy to make)
directions: In a skillet pan, melt butter.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Cook until done, 15 to 20 minutes on medium-high heat.
Then add can of white clam sauce.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat.
Add meat and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix, eggs and syrup in large bowl; beat on medium to high speed until blended, about 3 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until set.
Cool completely; cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and sugar; mix well, then stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until pie is set.
Cool.
Whip cream and use puffs as decoration around outer edge of pie.
Garnish alternate puffs of whipped cream with additional pecans and glazed chocolate chips if desired.

title: stew meat special
directions: Mix soups, mushrooms and flour.
Use casserole for meat and put onion on top.
Pour soup mixture on top of meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: chicken ruby
directions: Combine the flour and salt in a plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces and shake to coat.
Melt the butter in a large casserole and brown the chicken pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring just to a boil.
Pour over the chicken. Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Chill.
Roll in additional 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: electric peanut butter fudge
directions: Set heat at 280°.
Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter; stir until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch pan.

title: potatoes roasted provencale
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch dice.
In baking pan, toss potatoes, garlic and oil.
Roast at 425°, turning occasionally, for 25 minutes, or until golden.
Stir in olives, parsley, salt and pepper.

title: banana medley
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Pour mixture into 8 cup oiled mold and freeze at least 3 hours until firm. Unmold and let stand about 20 minutes at room temperature before serving.
Decorate with whipped cream and more well drained cling peaches.

title: cherry delight
directions: Put pie filling in a loaf pan.
Melt oleo.
Put white cake mix in a bowl; add oleo.
Stir with fork.
(This mixture does not need to be all mixed with the oleo.)
Put this mixture over the cherries.
Bake at 350° until top is brown to suit.

title: mom's tamale pie
directions: Brown beef in large skillet and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add other ingredients except water, cornmeal and salt.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes; set aside.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Put water in pan until dried.
Fry bacon; set aside.
Add onion, cabbage, vinegar and sugar.
Add bacon crumbled.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix up pudding according to directions on box. Add cream cheese and Cool Whip; mix well. Layer in container, starting with pudding mixture and ending with cookies.
Number of crushed cookies is as many as you like.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large saucepan; stir well. Place over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook until soft ball stage (232°).
Remove from heat. Add pecans and stir until well coated.
Spread on waxed paper and separate nuts with a fork.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chicken francese
directions: Saute chicken in lemon juice for two minutes.
Drain juice into separate bowl.
Dip cutlets in eggs.
Dab cutlets in flour on both sides.

title: pimentos and mushrooms
directions: Quarter peppers lengthwise.
Place on broiler pan, skin side up.
Flatten and place under broiler.
Cook until blackened and skins pop.
Layer in bowl, cover and let steam for 5 minutes. Uncover and peel skin off.
Reserve all juice from bowl and broiler pan.
Put all ingredients in saucepan; cover and bring to a boil.
Salt to taste.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add pineapple and oranges.
Mix all together.
Ready to eat or store and serve later.

title: lime delight
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: pudding mix(diabetic recipe)
directions: Sift dry milk granules and cornstarch together 3 times; mix with a fork.
Pack into a pint jar; cover tightly.
Store in a cool, dry place.
(For chocolate, add 1/2 cup cocoa.)

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oat balls
directions: Mix oats, peanut butter and vanilla in a large bowl and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over other mixture and mix until thick.
Drop, by spoonful, onto aluminum foil.
Cool and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute green onions and onion in margarine in large saucepan until limp and tender.
Add catsup, water, chili powder, sugar, liquid smoke, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Yields 7 1/2 cups.

title: coconut key lime bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend butter, salt, powdered sugar and 2 cups flour to make soft dough. Press evenly into 9 x 13 (ungreased) pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden. Combine eggs, lime peel, lime juice, sugar, food coloring and 1/4 cup flour and blend until smooth. Pour over baked crust. Sprinkle with coconut. Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes, until firm. Cool. Slice into bars.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and oleo, then add flour; mix well.
Slowly add milk; cook until thick.
(May need to add a little milk if too thick.)
Add all seasoning, egg yolks and crab meat.
Pour into glass dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done, then pull the meat off the bone. Now, you need a big pan.
Put 1 layer of chicken, chips, taco sauce, onion, olives, cheese, soup and sour cream.
Make second layer and bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Soften cheese and butter to room temperature. Mix salt and pepper into flour.
Stir into cheese and butter mixture.
Using cookie press, form into straws on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until very lightly browned around edges.
May also be rolled into balls and flattened with fork before baking.
May be frozen.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water and partially congeal.
Grind cranberries in a food chopper.
Chop orange sections fine.
Combine all ingredients and congeal.
Serves 18 to 20 people.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss chicken with parsley, celery, salt and pepper well.
Gently fold in whipped cream, mayo, lemon juice and almonds until well combined.
Refrigerate until well chilled, about one hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo with Cheez Whiz.
Heat 1 cup water with 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and cook until stems are tender.
Drain.
Place broccoli in baking dish with rice and soups and mix together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cottage cheese, sugar and cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream, then flour and mix well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven but leave cake in oven for 1 hour with heat off.

title: zucchini lasagne casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer spaghetti sauce, sliced zucchini, sweet peppers, onions, garlic and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Romano cheese on top.
Mushrooms are optional.
Keep repeating like making lasagna, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Romano cheese on the very top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: nanny's barbecue potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice; put in casserole dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over top of potatoes.
Slice onion and put on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato and hot dog casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook onion in oil until brown.
Mix flour, sugar and all seasonings; blend thoroughly with onion mixture.
Now add water.
Bring to a boil.
Cut hot dogs into chunks.
Layer potatoes and hot dogs in casserole.
Pour sauce over the top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour vinegar over the top.
Cover and return to oven for another 5 minutes.

title: quik chocolate frosting
directions: In small bowl, combine Nestle Quik and boiling water. Stir until Quik dissolves. Blend in butter and vanilla extract. Gradually beat in confectioners sugar. Continue beating at high speed until thick enough to spread. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: greek style salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, zucchini, cucumber, olives, onion and cheese in a large bowl, toss gently.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade.
Add artichokes to tomato mixture.
Combine reserved marinade, vinegar and pepper and pour over tomato mixture.
Toss. Cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain; serve on lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Trim tough stem ends of mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Set aside. With knife, slice mushroom caps thinly.
In a 4-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, in hot butter, cook sliced mushrooms and lemon juice until mushrooms are tender, stirring.
Reduce heat to medium-low. With slotted spoon, remove mushrooms to bowl.
In saucepan in remaining butter, cook onion and stems.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in flour until blended. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

Gradually stir in water and bouillon. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened. Into blender container, ladle half of the mixture. Cover and at high speed, blend until smooth. Repeat with the other half.
Return mixture to saucepan. Stir in salt, pepper, cream and mushroom slices.
Reheat just until soup is boiling.

title: french dressing
directions: In a jar or blender container, combine all ingredients.
Shake or blend dressing until thoroughly mixed.
Shake well before using.
Makes 250 ml. dressing.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat cooking oil in skillet.
Add green peppers.
Cook 5 minutes.
Combine soup mix in small bowl with water and liquid from pineapple.
Add to skillet and simmer covered 5 minutes. Combine vinegar, sugar and cornstarch in bowl and stir into meat. Add pineapple; cover and simmer until thick.

title: watercress-orange salad
directions: Wash, trim and cut watercress into small pieces; place in large bowl.
Cut endive in 1/4-inch pieces.
Peel and section oranges.
Add endive and orange sections to the watercress. Combine remaining ingredients in jar; blend well.
Pour over salad; toss gently.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add spices, then applesauce to which soda has been added.
Lastly add the flour, nuts and raisins. Bake in a slow oven at 375° for 1/2 hour, then at 400° for 1/2 hour or until it leaves pan.

title: cheese toast
directions: Boil milk.
Fry bread slices, one at a time, in margarine. Remove from margarine and drain on paper towel.
Place bread slices in milk until moist.
Season to taste and place in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake for five minutes in hot oven.
(Optional:
Top with mild salsa.)
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour, sugar, orange peel, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, with wire whip or fork, beat milk, peanut butter, margarine and egg until well mixed.
Stir peanut butter mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and heat; do not boil.
Resist the urge to use tomato stuff like catsup, sauce, etc.
It burns black on the meat.
Good on beef, pork and chicken.
Baste often.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place hot pepper and garlic in hot sterilized jars. Remove part of stem from each okra pod. Pack okra into jars. Add dill seeds.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Mix in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit soup
directions: Place water into mixing bowl.
Sprinkle tapioca over water, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add sugar, orange juice and salt. Let stand 20 minutes.
Add pineapple, oranges and bananas.
If tapioca mixture seems too thick, add a little pineapple juice. Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: impossible to fail pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 10-inch greased (or larger) pie pan.
Bake 1 hour until set. Do not use smaller pie pan.

title: peanut butter and jelly crisps
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in 3-quart pan over low heat. Add marshmallows and stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Press half of mixture into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spread with jelly and top with remaining cream mixture, pressing gently. Chill and cut into squares.

title: ham appetizers
directions: Make cheese pastry.
Cut into rounds.
Put 1 teaspoon ham filling in center of pastry round.
Fold over and crimp with fork. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: hot peppers and dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs and peppers.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, ketchup, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add peppers and hot dogs. Cook 10 minutes.
Put into jars.
Pressure cook 5 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
This recipe works well using chunked, cooked deer meat instead of dogs.

title: weight watchers watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with pineapple and its juice. Stir in yogurt. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill. Each serving is 1/2 cup.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and molasses.
Mix flour and cocoa together.
Add soda to hot water and add to creamed mixture, then add flour mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a tube or Bundt pan.

title: baklava
directions: You will need a 10 x 15-inch pan, pastry brush and electric knife.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve lime and lemon Jell-O.
Add mayonnaise; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients; let set in fridge.

title: simple sweet scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into a large bowl; stir to mix well.
Add butter and cut in with a pastry blender or rub in with your fingers until the mixture looks like fine granules.
Add sugar; toss to mix.
Add milk and stir with a fork until a soft dough forms.
Form dough into a ball; put onto a lightly floured board and give 10 to 12 kneads.

title: baked apricots
directions: Grease casserole, alternate a layer of apricots with the cracker crumbs and brown sugar, making two layers. Pour melted butter over all and bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber-anchovy hors d'oeuvres
directions: Place cucumber slice on a round toast bed or Wheat Thin.
In the center of the cucumber, squeeze a small circle of anchovy paste.
Press a stuffed olive slice into the paste.

title: pumpkin gobs
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: weight watchers pie
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, peanut butter and honey together. Press firmly in large deep pie plate or glass dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Slice bananas and cover krispie crust with them. Mix pudding according to directions on box and pour over bananas. Top with Cool Whip. May sprinkle with nuts or Rice Krispies if desired.

title: lemony carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, beat margarine 30 seconds.
Add sugar, lemon peel and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour mixture and yogurt alternately, beating after each addition.
Stir in carrots.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cake with Lemon Yogurt Frosting.
Garnish as desired.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onions in margarine until tender. Combine Chicken a la King, cooked onion, chilies, all spices and 1 1/2 cups of the grated cheese. This is the filling.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix together real good.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, make out rolls on counter top (12 inches long).
Use cookie sheets and bake at 325° for about 2 hours, turning often.
Wrap in foil while warm.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer.
Can also use this recipe for deer jerky.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple, flour and sugar.
Cook until bubbly and thick.
Stir in Jell-O.
Cool.
Slice bananas and place in pie shells.
Pour filling over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and lightly beaten eggs.
Add mixture of sugar, cornstarch, salt, mustard and onion.
Stir in milk and butter. Add to corn and egg mixture.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole. Bake in 400°
oven for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in butter and salt (cut meat in bite size cubes). Remove meat. Add onion and pepper. Saute. Return meat. Add tomato sauce, bouillon cube, soy sauce and sugar.
A little water may be added, if needed. Simmer until meat is tender. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: rum coconut bonbons
directions: In medium bowl, sift vanilla wafer crumbs, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and salt.
In small bowl, whisk rum and corn syrup until blended.
Stir into crumb mixture until dough is moist enough to hold together.
Add coconut.
Immediately roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place rum balls in airtight container and refrigerate overnight to mellow.
Spread top of each ball with melted semi-sweet chocolate.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook
chicken
until
tender;
season
to taste.
Place chicken in baking dish or pan.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed together in bowl.
Pour mixture over chicken.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place bread in bottom of pan.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese style chicken salad
directions: Mix well in a medium bowl the soy sauce, mustard, ginger and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in cooked chicken and green onions to coat well.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Before serving, stir in vegetables.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Serves 4.

title: peanut brittle
directions: You will need to butter a cookie sheet or pizza pan (at least 1/4 to 1/2-inch deep) and set to the side.
In a cast-iron skillet, mix sugar, syrup and peanuts on high heat until mixture boils to a color one shade darker then you want your brittle to be.
You must stir often.
This takes about 15 to 25 minutes, depending on how hot your stove gets.
After mixture reaches desired color, completely remove from heat.
Quickly stir in baking soda.
Be careful!
As soon as the baking soda hits the mixture it will begin to foam and grow.
Pour onto your buttered cookie sheet and let stand until completely cooled.
Break apart and enjoy the easiest peanut brittle ever.

title: luke's easy pizzas
directions: Break muffins open.
Spread pizza sauce on muffin.
Place pepperoni slices on top of sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly.

title: quick breakfast roll treat
directions: Split roll.
Brown uncut side.
Spread cut side with butter. Place 1 teaspoon any jelly or jam in center.
Brown until butter and jelly are melted and bread is brown.
Serve with fruit in season.

title: noda's pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and add all ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs last.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; add to fruit cocktail.
Hand beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons fruit cocktail juice over mixture in pan.
On top of this, sprinkle brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Should be golden brown.
Serve warm or cool with Cool Whip topping.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Beat eggs and oil.
Add apples and sugar, then all other dry ingredients.
Then the nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: golden cornbread ring
directions: Spray 9-inch round dish and outside of glass custard cup with vegetable oil.
Coat dishes with cornflake crumbs.
Invert custard cup in center of baking dish.
Mix together corn muffin mix and biscuit baking mix.
Add egg and milk.
Pour into dish.
Bake in Radarange oven 4 minutes on Low.
Turn dish halfway through cooking.
Bake additional 2 minutes on High.
Turn halfway through cooking.
Let set 10 minutes.
Invert on platter.
Yields 5 servings.

title: slush
directions: Juice the lemons and oranges and mix with sugar and Ginger Ale.
Freeze.
Stir while mixture is freezing.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir vegetable mixture into egg and cheese mixture.
Pat crescent dough into the bottom and up sides of a 2-quart rectangular Pyrex dish.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture onto crust and spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage and polish sausagedallas, texas
directions: In a large pot, put 2 Tbsp. of cooking oil.
Cut link sausage into 1/2-inch long pieces and brown on all sides.
Into the pot add cabbage cut into fairly large pieces.

title: eggs portugal
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam, place bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit and 1/3 cup sugar.
Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Make a batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Batter should be thicker than cake dough.
Pour batter on top of melted butter and don't stir.
Place fruit on top of batter; don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: Mix olive oil, oregano, basil and thyme and set aside.
Saute chicken in 1 tablespoon olive oil and garlic. When cooked, add tomatoes and parsley.
Saute 5 more minutes.
Cook linguine in boiling water 3 minutes.
Drain.
In a large bowl, toss chicken mixture with noodles and cheese.
Add oil and spice mixture.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Put dried beef in blender.
Save enough to roll ham.
Add to cream cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish.
Form into a ball.
Roll in leftover dried beef.

title: virginia's orange salad
directions: Mix jello, pudding and water in 1-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cool and refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and whip.
Fold in pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and marshmallows.
Add nuts, coconut and Cool Whip.
This makes 1/2 gallon of salad.

title: one dish meal
directions: Slice the chicken breast.
Cook broccoli in small amount of water until just tender.
Drain.
Lay broccoli in greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken slices on top.
Add water to soup and pour over.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted.
A simple, quick and nutritious all in one meal.
Serves 1 or 2 people, all from one dish and maybe some leftovers.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 7 ingredients in order given in a clear glass bowl (for eye appeal).
Mix the mayonnaise and sour cream. Spread on top. Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full of batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 (2-inch) muffins or 36 small muffins.
While baking, make topping:

title: johnnycake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place baking pan in oven to heat with 2 tablespoons of Crisco.
In mixing bowl, add all remaining ingredients.
Mix
on low speed until all ingredients are mixed. Take
pan out of oven.
Pour melted Crisco into mixing bowl.
Stir until
mixed.
Pour mixture into hot pan.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: yummies
directions: Melt chocolate bits on stove.
Remove and add condensed milk and nuts.
Spoon out on waxed paper.

title: meat loaf
directions: Hand mix together, except tomato sauce.
Pour tomato sauce over top of meat loaf.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours (drain fat) at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: mom's squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoonfuls into hot, buttered frying pan.
Cook until golden brown, turning while cooking.
Serve with syrup of your choice.

title: pastitsio
directions: Toss pasta with butter and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: easy fresh apple cake
directions: Put apples in bowl.
Break eggs over and stir with old wooden spoon.
Add sugar, cinnamon, oil and nuts. Add flour, salt and soda.
Beat with spoon until creamy.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: asphodel bread
directions: Sift biscuit mix, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Soften the yeast in warm milk (not hot).
Beat eggs with cream of tartar until thoroughly broken up.
Combine milk and eggs and pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Should be heavy and sticky. Set aside in a warm place covered with a damp towel or plastic wrap.
When doubled, stir down and fill oiled loaf pans about halfway.
Let double again before baking at 350° for 20 minutes. This bread freezes well.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
This may be baked in iron skillet or in corn stick or muffin pans, which have been lightly sprayed with Pam.
Makes about 15 muffins. I prefer iron cornstick pan.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream remaining 1 cup butter, gradually adding 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour with baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.

title: scotties
directions: Melt together ingredients.
Add oatmeal.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add bananas and nuts.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Add to mixture.
Bake in 1 loaf pan at 350` for 45 minutes.

title: i love you cookies
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter, sugar and vanilla on	medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in corn syrup and
egg
yolks.
Stir
in flour and salt until blended. Refrigerate
dough	30 minutes.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. In small
bowl,
lightly
beat
egg
whites.
Dip balls in egg whites and
roll
in walnuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
With thumb, make deep indentation in center of each cookie.
Bake
at
325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with cherry filling.

title: wine punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix and serve immediately.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, pierce with fork and place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out insides.
Mash insides with fork.
Add butter, cheese and bacon bits.
Put mixture back in potato shells.
Place on baking sheet and bake another 10 minutes.

title: frozen almond punch
directions: Make syrup
by
bringing
sugar
and
4 cups water to a boil. Pour
boiling syrup over gelatin and cool.
Add juices, gallon of water and almond extract.
Pour into punch bowl and freeze. Remove
from
freezer
about
5 hours before serving. Stir until slushy.
Yield:
5 to 6 gallons.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, melt butterscotch chips and margarine.
Add brown sugar; mix well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg slightly and add with vanilla to sugar mixture.
Sift in dry ingredients .
Mix well by hand.
Fold in marshmallows and chocolate chips.
May add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Bring juice to boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Set aside until starts to thicken.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold until set.

title: salmon pie
directions: Deep dish pastry pie pan.
Make double pastry shell.
Mix all ingredients.
Fill shell.
Cover with other pastry.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Brush egg white over top.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a small baking dish with the butter.
Place the cabbage in the prepared baking dish.
Combine the cream, sweetener, salt and paprika.
Pour over the cabbage and stir lightly to mix.
Cover the dish and bake for about 45 minutes.
Remove the dish from the oven and heat the broiler. Sprinkle the cheese over the top of the cabbage and broil for 2 or 3 minutes, until the cheese melts.

title: golden eagle pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Sprinkle nuts in unbaked pie shell and add filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture doesn't adhere to knife.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer. Use with fresh strawberries, apple slices, etc.

title: sour cream
directions: Blend all ingredients, except additional water.
Pour blended ingredients into a saucepan.
Rinse blender with additional water and pour into pan.
Lightly boil, stirring, about 10 minutes, until thickened.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Put into casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine pie filling and pineapple, including juice.
Place in bottom of ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
In another bowl combine pecans, coconut and cake mix (dry).
Place on top of fruit evenly. Chop margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: maple-glazed mixed fruit
directions: Cut the pear and apple into 3/4 inch pieces. Toss with raisins. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet. When it sizzles, add the fruit and cook, stirring gently, for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in maple syrup and cinnamon; cook until the fruit begins to soften and the sauce is slightly thickened, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat and gently stir in the vanilla. Serve over pancakes or waffles. Also good with yogurt or ice cream.

title: fig cookies
directions: In one bowl, cream vanilla, sugar and Crisco; add milk and eggs and mix.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add to first mixture slowly, mixing well.
Roll out on floured board and divide dough.
Chop 1 pint fig preserves.
Roll cake dough into large square.
Spread figs on 1/2 of dough.
Fold dough over and cut into bars.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Cookies will not brown on top but will on bottom.

title: upside-down apple pie
directions: Arrange nuts, flat side up, in butter in deep 9-inch pie pan. Pat brown sugar over nuts and cover with round of pastry rolled 1/8-inch thick; trim edges.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add everything else.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: c-sharp cheddar muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin pan with Pam or similar. Put flour in bowl; cut in cold butter.
Add cheese and milk.
Mix into a dough.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until muffins are golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Chop eggs.
Mix with soup and water.
Put layer of cracker crumbs, layer of asparagus and layer of cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Put ham in baking pan or dish.
Mix sugar, mustard and pineapple juice.
Cover ham with this mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Add pineapple slices and brown.
This is for the thick slice.

title: fresh cranberry cake
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, buttermilk, eggs, oil, orange rind, nuts, dates and cranberries together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and pour a mixture of 1 cup sugar and orange juice over cake.
Drip and pour over again.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Add nuts and apples; mix well.
Bake in a 10 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased, at 325° for 60 minutes, or until done.

title: spicy cranberry punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and spices.
Cover.
Steep five minutes.
Remove tea bags and stir in sugar.
Cool.
Add next four ingredients and chill.
Garnish with orange slices studded with cloves if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: carrot mold
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a well-greased 5 1/2-cup ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve on platter with cooked peas in center.

title: sweet potato casserole with crisp topping
directions: Mash sweet potatoes that have been well drained.
Add eggs, milk and 3/4 stick of butter and vanilla.
Mix well and place in greased casserole dish.
Top with topping made by combining brown sugar, 1/2 cup softened butter or margarine, flour and broken pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add blueberry juice.
Chill until flabby.
Whip gelatin and add the drained blueberries, pineapple and chopped pecans.
Fold in whipped
cream. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken barbecue sauce 1
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Let cool.
Then add egg. Pour over chicken and let soak all day or overnight, turning chicken once (avoid an aluminum pan).
Brush on chicken as it is being barbecued.

title: "sin" dessert
directions: Put a layer of vanilla pudding, then chocolate pudding and continue to layer until all is used, then layer with Cool Whip. Can add shaved chocolate on top.
Chill overnight.
Yields 20 servings.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cook black beans as you would pinto beans.
Puree 6 cups of the cooked beans.
Blend beans with stock in a saucepan.
Season with cumin, butter and salt to taste.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir in juice of 1 lime and chopped green onions.
Serve with sliced limes and sour cream. 4 servings.

title: korean spaghetti
directions: Heat large frying pan with sesame seed oil.
Add diced carrots, diced scallions and bacon bits.
Add a dash of soy sauce and let simmer under low flame until carrots are soft.
Remove from flame and set aside.
Boil spaghetti (or linguine) in a large pot until cooked (preferably al dente).
Drain well.
Add carrots, scallions and bacon bits mixture to spaghetti and toss thoroughly. Add soy sauce to taste.
Serve hot or room temperature.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put yeast in warm milk and dissolve.
Let stand about 10 minutes, then add oil, sugar, salt and eggs to milk mixture.
Add flour gradually.
Let rise in bowl at least 2 hours or more.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into strips.
Dip each strip in melted butter.
Stack around in a Bundt pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage and beef. Drain.
In crock-pot melt cheeses. Add meat, soup, tomatoes, green chilies and onions.
Mix well. Makes a large amount and can be frozen.
Serve with chips.

title: braised pork coriander
directions: Remove excess fat and cut the pork into 1-inch cubes.
Scrub potatoes and cut in half; do not peel.
Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown the potatoes and pork.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems. When the pork and potatoes are browned, move them to one side of the pan and add mushrooms.
Saute quickly; combine with potatoes and pork.
Reduce heat; add wine and season to taste with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with ground coriander.
Cover.
Simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes or until pork and potatoes are done.

title: cindy's icing
