directions: Beat all of the ingredients together except warm milk.
Blend well.
Slowly add in the warm mild and continue to beat at least 40 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Cook peas according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain.
Combine peas and remaining ingredients, cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook (for the sauce) the butter, syrup, brown sugar and baking soda on High for 3 minutes.
In 2 large paper bags, place the popped corn and the sauce.
Shake well; may want to stir a little. Return entire bag
to microwave for 2 minutes.
Shake again. Return bag to microwave for 2 minutes.
Great snack for kids.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and drain all fruit except pineapple.
Add instant vanilla pudding and stir.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Saute in foaming margarine until transparent.
Add flour then beef stock.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour in soup bowls.
Add sliced French bread.
Top with grated cheese.
Broil just until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: penuche(brown sugar fudge)
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and milk.
Cook until sugar dissolves; continue cooking on medium heat to soft ball stage*.
Cool without stirring.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy.
Pour in buttered pan; cool and cut in squares.
Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put Cool Whip also on top of pie.
Chill pie 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt over low heat the butter or oleo.
Remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut bars while still warm.

title: sausage scramble
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook and stir sausage until light brown; drain.
Place sausage in greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in cheese.
Pour egg mixture on sausage.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake uncovered until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with tomato slices, if desired.
Makes 18 servings.

title: lemon butter
directions: Add cornstarch to sugar; mix in lemon rind. Add lemon juice, water and butter.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix and serve with corn chips.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put dinner rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with the pudding mix.
In a saucepan, melt the margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls. Sprinkle chopped nuts over.
Cover and let rise 8 to 10 hours or overnight; do not refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Turn onto plate with sides to hold juice.
Serve warm.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine water, potatoes, luncheon meat, corn and onion. Bring to boil on high setting.
Cover; turn to low and simmer for
15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Serve.

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in an unbaked 9 inch pie shell.

title: spaghetti and ham fiorentina
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, prepare spinach as label directs; drain.
Prepare spaghetti in saucepan; boil and drain. Cut oleo into small pieces; add spinach, milk, Ricotta cheese, basil and walnuts.
Over medium heat, heat until mixture is hot, tossing gently to mix well.
Stir in ham and heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: creamy coconut frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 12 minutes or until thickened to consistency of a pudding.
Remove from heat and stir in coconut.
Cool completely before frosting cake.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender-crisp; drain.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Heat other ingredients until hot; pour over.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: beets with orange sauce
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add orange juice and butter.
Cook for 5 minutes in top of double boiler over very low heat.
Add beets and let stand for several hours.
Reheat and serve very hot.

title: oat cake
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water over 1 cup oats; let stand 20 minutes. Cream 1 stick butter. Add 1 cup sugar, brown sugar, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well. Add oat mixture. Add 1/2 cup flour. Mix well. Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 pan for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza potato topper
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook pepper, basil and oregano until pepper is tender.
Stir in soup, water and pepperoni.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture over potatoes.
Top with cheese.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Beat sugar, cocoa, oleo, eggs, vanilla and salt together until fluffy.
Alternately add flour and milk to batter mixture.
Beat slowly until blended.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bright tomato marinade
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously. Combine tomatoes and onion in a shallow container. Pour dressing over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
To serve, use slotted spoon.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: lethal recipe for roaches
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Mix well and shape in small balls about the size of marbles.
Place these in places where you think roaches may hide:

under large appliances such as dishwasher, stoves, refrigerators, washing machines or dryers, in cabinets, under burners of your stove and any dark, warm spot. Roaches thrive in these breeding places.
Just make sure no children or pets can come in contact with this poison as it is toxic and can make them sick.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Add sugar, bead molasses, soy sauce, onion and celery.
Add enough water to keep from burning.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add Chinese vegetables. Continue cooking until vegetables are heated.
Mix cornstarch with cold water; use to thicken gravy.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Cook all ingredients, except sugar, until well blended.
Put through juicer; add sugar.
Heat to boiling point; pour into sterilized jars and seal.
When serving, add some lemon juice, if you like.

title: julia's special salad
directions: Tear greens into bite size pieces.
Combine with artichokes and palm hearts in a large salad bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over greens until all are coated. Deliciously different.

title: dill sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour until well blended.
Add stock, gradually, while stirring, then cook slowly for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add dill, vinegar and sugar.
Season to taste.
Remove from heat and add egg yolk.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves until limp.
Cool.
Cook rice.
Mix together meat, eggs, rice and 1/2 can mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Place small portion of meat mixture into cabbage leaf and roll, folding edges and ends.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Arrange rolls in bottom of baking dish or roaster.
Mix remaining portion of soup with tomato paste and pour over the rolls.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
You can line the bottom of pan with extra cabbage leaves if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of celery or chicken soup and broth together until hot.
Mix margarine, flour and milk together.
Take cooked chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour
hot broth and soup over chicken.
Pour margarine, flour and milk mixture over chicken. Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly done.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken soup

title: strawberry banana jello salad
directions: Mix everything but sour cream and spread half of mixture in dish.
Cover with sour cream.
Put in rest of mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, cornmeal and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt, corn and green pepper.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into eggs.
Stir constantly and add remaining hot mixture.

title: e z chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take out of pan, cool and debone chicken.
Add to a saucepan, gravy mix, mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup.
Fill soup cans with broth that chicken was boiled in and add to chicken.
Cook all together on low for 30 to 45 minutes.
If too thick add more broth.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: cake in a hurry
directions: Beat eggs well slowly.
Add sugar. In a separate bowl beat shortening until creamy. Add 1 cup flour, then add to sugar mixture.
Mix well. Add milk and remaining flour, salt and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: * Put small amounts of oatmeal in blender until it turns to powder.
Measure out 5 cups of oatmeal and only "powderize" that, (not 5 cups of "powderized" oatmeal).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all the ingredients and mix together in casserole dish. Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup over this.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate thumbprint cookies
directions: In small mixer bowl beat butter, sugar, egg yolk, milk and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until blended. Refrigerate dough until firm enough to handle.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl.
Pour Jell-O over it.
Stir well. Add pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Stir well. Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil over medium - high heat. Add onion and peppers, cook until tender. Add chicken, corn, broth and salsa. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice, cover. Remove from heat. Let stand for 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Sprinkle in 1 cup cheese and stir. Pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over top let stand for 2 minutes and serve.

title: mini "white castles"
directions: Brown beef.
Add cheese, onion soup and mayonnaise.
Cook until mixed.
Slice rolls in half and spread meat mixture on bottom half; cover with top.
Top each roll with pickle slice if desired.

title: taco sauce
directions: In a large pan, heat the vinegar, sugar, chili powder, salt, oregano, bay leaves and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and cook 2 hours.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
ingredients
in
order as listed. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
You can also add 1 cup pineapple, if you want.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone, breaking into small pieces in large casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar, Jell-O, cake mix and water on top.
Put butter on top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries.
Mix pineapple, bananas and nuts; add to Jell-O.
Pour half of the mixture into a 12 x 8-inch dish. Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream. Gently pour remaining mixture on sour cream. Refrigerate until congealed and ready to serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer lasagna noodles, meat, spaghetti sauce and Velveeta cheese slices.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hamburger stroganoff(serves 4)
directions: In a large, heavy frying pan, saute the beef in the butter along with the garlic, 1 medium onion and mushrooms until beef has lost its pinkness and vegetables are tender.
Add the flour; mix until blended.
Add the beef broth, salt, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Blend in the sour cream. Keep warm, but do not boil.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil together.
Set aside and completely cool.

title: chicken-on-a-shoestring salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except shoestring potatoes and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, fold in shoestrings. Serve salad on lettuce leaves. Add fresh fruit, hot muffins and iced tea for a light, tasty lunch.

title: creole beans
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in margarine until tender. Mix in remaining ingredients and cook until beans are heated thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: snappy tomato juice
directions: Heat all ingredients in large kettle to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently until tomatoes are soft. Remove and discard onion and bay leaf.
Press mixture through food mill or sieve.
Heat juice just until boiling.
Fill prepared jars and cover with seals.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on.
Peel and slice potatoes thinly into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
In small saucepan, mix together 1/2 cup butter, soup, cheese, onions and sour cream. Stir over low heat just until heated through and pour over potatoes.
In small skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter and add cornflake crumbs.
Mix well.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crescent sausage rolls(hot hot hot!!!!!)
directions: Lay crescent rolls out on pan. Do not separate. Leave all in one piece. Spread mustard on top of rolls. Crumble sausage on top of rolls. Roll like jelly rolls; put in freezer for 20 to 40 minutes. Cut and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jodi's tuna casserole
directions: Mix togehter first 5 ingredients.
Cook and drain macaroni, place in large casserole dish, then add first 5 ingredients and some cheese.
Top with cheese and 1 small bag chips.
Cover and bake at 375° to 400° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: peach pie
directions: Place fruit in shell.
Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Remove from heat, add Jell-O.
Mix and pour over fruit in pie shell.
Let set.
Serve with whip cream or ice cream.
Can use strawberries instead of peaches.

title: berries and bits pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix milk and water.
Add pudding; beat well. Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 2 cups pudding into a 3-quart serving bowl.
Layer with half of each:
vanilla wafers, strawberries and chocolate morsels.
Repeat once more. Chill; keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add beans and mix remaining ingredients.
Line bottom of pan with Doritos.
Pour hamburger mixture in pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and zucchini.
Stir in raisins, nuts, vanilla and fruit cocktail.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let dough rise.
Squeeze sausage out of casing and lightly brown in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Mix in other ingredients and cool.
Roll out dough into approximately 9 x 12-inch rectangle. Spread sausage mix over dough.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut roll in half.
Lightly brush top of rolls with oil.
Sprinkle garlic salt on top (optional).
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden.
Cool before serving.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs into the milk.
Add sugar and rice; stir.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into well buttered 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until set.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar. Press in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and simmer 5 minutes. Cook the hamburger until brown. Drain off fat.
Add 3/4 cup of the tomato sauce to the meat. Flatten out crescent rolls and press two together to form square (4 squares).
Place approximately 1/4 hamburger mixture on each rectangle.
Top with 1/2 slice American cheese. Bring up corners of dough to meet and pinch together to seal all openings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Add 1/3 cup water and any remaining hamburger mixture to tomato sauce and simmer gently while pies are baking. Sauce can be spooned over pies at the table.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a square baking pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, sugar, butter and salt in a large pan.
Bring to a boil and add rice.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and add 1/2 to mixture.
Stir constantly.
Add rest of eggs and cook for several minutes but do not boil.
Add vanilla.
Pour into serving dishes and cool.

title: mae's apple pie
directions: Slice apples into frying pan; add butter.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon together.
Add to apples and butter; heat until good and hot.
Pour into pie crust; add top crust or strips across.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients with mixer.
Add carrots and nuts. Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Follow directions for cake layers.

title: country kitchen calico bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter beans in stockpot and bring to a boil.
Simmer until beans are tender, about 2 hours. Add butter beans.
Makes about 1 gallon soup or about 16 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into bottom of 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour; then debone and cut into small pieces.
Saute onion (chopped) and bell pepper (chopped) until soft.
Add chili powder and mix well.
Add soups, water and broth. Layer tortillas in a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Cover with a layer of chicken pieces; then cover with soup mixture.
Repeat layering until chicken, soup mixture and tortillas are used.
Top with Ro-Tel tomatoes, then Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled or baked neck bones
directions: Clean and wash
neck
bones.
Place in pot.
Cover with water and cook for
hour in the covered pot.
After 1 hour, add the onions,
celery,
carrots,
salt,
pepper
and Accent. Cover and boil another hour or until the meat is tender.

title: walnut carrot and raisin loaf
directions: Resift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs together well.
Stir in carrot and lemon peel, then flour mixture, blending until all flour is moistened.
Set aside 2 tablespoons walnuts for top of loaf.
Stir remaining walnuts and raisins into the batter and turn into greased loaf pan; sprinkle with reserved walnuts.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake below center of oven at 350°
about 1 hour, until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Place on wire rack.
Cool.

title: crackle top molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add brown sugar.
Blend in egg and molasses. Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift the dry ingredients and gradually blend into creamed mixture.
(Dough should be soft, but not sticky.)
Add vanilla and lemon.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a greased baking sheet.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and remove from baking sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: mince soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place beef in a large pot or crock-pot. Add turnips, potatoes and onions.
Mash carrots and add to other ingredients.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes and turnips are soft.

title: amish potatoes supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well all ingredients, except hash browns and chips.
Stir in hash browns.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with potato chips.
Bake for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: swedish cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion until onion is tender; drain.
Add tomatoes and rice, stirring to blend tomatoes.
Blend thoroughly. Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn off heat.
Let stand 10 minutes, then stir in next 5 ingredients and heat until cheese is melted. Arrange cabbage in bottom of an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Spread meat mixture over cabbage.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: jogging in a jar
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drink 2 cups daily.
Keep refrigerated.
This drink helps to lower high blood pressure and lower high cholesterol.

title: cheesy chicken bagel melt
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, cheese, garlic powder and dry mustard; blend well.
Stir in broccoli and chicken.
Spoon mixture onto 6 bagel halves and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Yield: 6 sandwiches.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt in top of double boiler Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk.
Cool.
Whip 1 package of Dream Whip and fold into mixture. Pour into crust and chill.
Top with the other package of Dream Whip (prepared according to package directions) or 9 ounces Cool Whip.

title: mudd pudding
directions: Crush cookies.
Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Make pudding with milk and powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Fold in crushed cookies.
Sprinkle some on top.

title: dirt cups
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Stir Cool Whip and 1/2 cookies into pudding.
Put 1 tablespoon of cookies into the bottom of cups. Fill each cup about 3/4 full of pudding mixture. Top each cup with the rest of the crushed cookies.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix ground beef with cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and milk. Spread out on a cookie sheet (about 1-inch thick).
Chill.
When firm, cut into squares.
Flour each square and brown in shortening.
Place in baking dish.
Dilute soup with milk and pour over squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mint patties
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let chill two hours.
Make into patties the size of a quarter.
Chill until firm.
Dip into chocolate and paraffin that has been melted in the top of a double boiler.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving. Serve with vegetables or chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Drain salmon; reserve juice.
Melt butter.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk; stir until thickened.
Add salmon liquid. Season to taste.
Flake salmon; add to sauce.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put raisins in saucepan; cover with water.
Simmer 20 minutes uncovered.
Drain but save 3/4 cup of broth.
Let cool.
Mix applesauce, flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Blend oil, artificial sweetener and egg until light and fluffy, then add above dry ingredients alternately with reserved raisin liquid.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured mold pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: honey-soy chicken sandwich
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of first 6 ingredients 4 to 6 hours.
Cook chicken on grill and toast rolls.
Serve with lettuce, tomato and mustard.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, ketchup, grated onion and Miracle Whip together, then add crabmeat.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours or longer.
Serve with crackers or whatever.

title: strawberry & sour cream jell-o salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Put one half of mixture in a glass bowl and place in refrigerator to set.
When set; spread sour cream on set mixture.
Spoon remaining Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Return to refrigerator to set.
(Very pretty salad.)

title: quick sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute celery and onion with sausage.
Pour off part of the grease. Add rice and noodles from mix and brown. Add seasoning package from mix and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Combine sugar and baking cocoa in bowl. Stir in evaporated milk, eggs, butter and vanilla, blending well. Stir in coconut and pecans; turn into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until set around the edges. Cool on racks. Makes 2 pies, 6 to 8 servings each.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in pot and add onions. Cook until brown. Add bell peppers, onion tops, garlic and parsley flakes. Continue to smother down until dark brown. Add Ro-Tel, shrimp or sausage. Smother together until sausage is starting to cook. Add cayenne pepper, Tony's seasoning and hot sauce. Once your sauce is cooking, add water (about 4 cups) and let cook on medium heat until thick. Add rice to pot with water (add water to just above first knuckle on middle finger over rice). Add salt. Stir together and cover. Cook on low to medium heat until rice is tender (about 1/2 hour).

title: peaches 'n' cream delight
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon. Heat while stirring to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal.
Press into bottom of 9-inch pie plate or square pan. Spread softened ice cream in crust.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving, top with peaches.

title: good "nanner" pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed. Fold in sour cream and half of the whipped topping. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding until gone. Top with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate. Makes a large bowl full!

title: apple spice pudding
directions: Prepare pudding with milk according to directions; set aside. In nonstick skillet, combine
apple juice, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon and bring to a boil.
Add apples and raisins and cook until tender.
Stir frequently until juice is reduced, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add to pudding.
Stir.
Divide into 4 servings and cover until set.
To serve, top each cup with 1 tablespoon of whipped topping and nutmeg.
Serves 4.
Contains 138 calories, 1 gm fat and 401 mg sodium.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chop vegetables (bite-size).
Mix with all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Pat into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks, milk and vanilla to make custard. Place a layer of vanilla wafers in baking dish, then place a layer of bananas until dish is full.
Pour over this the cooked custard. Beat egg whites stiff; add 2 teaspoons sugar and beat again.
Put egg whites on pudding and brown.

title: creamy chicken-n-pasta
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in nonstick skillet.
Cook chicken until browned, 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese, 2/3 cup fried onions and noodles.
Simmer, stirring, until hot.
Microwave 2/3 cup onions 1 minute; sprinkle over noodles.
Garnish with chopped parsley and tomatoes, if you like.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, crushed pineapple, oil, and eggs together with a whisk NOT A MIXER.
Bake in 9x13 inch pan for approximately 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cake cool completely before frosting.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in nuts and pineapple.
Pour into 2 ready made graham cracker crusts.
Put in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving. This pie will keep up to 1 month in the freezer.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring the water and salt to a good boil. Stir in the grits. When water returns to a boil, reduce heat and cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. When done, stir in the cheese. Add the butter. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush 1 (3 row) package of Oreos.
Mix with melted butter. Soften ice cream and set aside.
Place cookie crust in large Pyrex dish.
Spread softened ice cream over crust.
Set in freezer until ice cream is firm.
Soften hot fudge in microwave oven and pour over ice cream.
Place in freezer until firm.
Spread chopped nuts over fudge.
Soften caramel topping and pour over nut layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: fruited sweet potato escallop
directions: Mix potatoes with flour and seasonings.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into buttered casserole.
Cover and bake 50 minutes.
Uncover during last 10 minutes of cooking to allow the top to brown.
Serve in dish used in baking.

title: bobbie's layered vegetable salad
directions: In a covered 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the lettuce, celery, onions, peppers and peas in that order.
Spread the mayonnaise over the top.
On top of the mayonnaise, sprinkle the cheese, then the eggs and tomatoes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hamburger gravy - s.o.s.
directions: In a large skillet brown hamburger and remove fat.
Add flour and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until desired consistency.
Serve with toast or hot biscuits.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Marinate meat in vinegar, onions, honey and spices 4 hours or overnight.
Brown meat and cook onions, salt and pepper; cover with marinade.
Roast, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes per pound, plus 20 minutes.
Thicken pan juices with gingersnaps.

title: philly cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add fruit juice.
Chill until partially set.
Use mixer and blend cream cheese into jello, then add cream which has been whipped.
Add fruit and nuts.
Place in jello mold or square pan.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: cheese cracker spread
directions: Place all the ingredients in a food processor and chop for 3 to 5 seconds.
Add mayonnaise (enough to moisten).
Spread on Wheat Thins crackers.

title: deviled lamb shanks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season lamb shanks with salt and pepper. Coat shanks with flour.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon till crisp. Drain and reserve 1/4 c. dripping x 2 Tbsp. bacon. Microwave
beans per package directions.
Add mushrooms and onions to the 1/4 c. dripping in a skillet. Cook on med-high heat 10 min. Drain. Add bacon, hot cooked green beans, and pepper.
Mix lightly and pour into 2 quart dish. Microwave cheese and pour over green beans. Sprinkle with bacon.

title: kids cooler
directions: Put 3 ice cubes into bottom of glasses. Pour 1/3 c.
pineapple juice into each glass adda squeeze of lime then 1/3 c. orange juice. Garnish with fruit.

title: butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in margarine until coarse crumbs.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix with hands to form smooth dough.
Shape into balls.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Roll in sugar.
Roll again when cool.

title: shrimp stuffed celery
directions: Combine ingredients. Stuff celery that has been cut in 2-3 inch pieces.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts and ice cream) until smooth. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake pie until side begins to pull away from pan and top springs back when lightly touched with fingers about 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: crispy potato pancakes (latkes)
directions: Using a box grater or food processor, coarsely grate potatoes and onions. Put grated potatoes and onions together in cheesecloth or a tea towel and twist it to squeeze out the excess liquid. Put the dry potatoes and onions in a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Fold in the egg whites and chives to bind the mixture together. Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat and coat with 1/4 inch of oil. For each pancake, take about 2 Tbsp. of potato mixture and drop into the hot oil; gently flatten with a spatula so they fry up thin and crispy. Fry for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until golden. Remove to paper towels to drain; season with salt while the potato pancakes are still hot. Continue frying, adding more oil as needed, until all the mixture is used up. Serve immediately with applesauce, if desired.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Dip each chop in buttermilk.
Roll in wheat germ, coating it as heavily as possible.
Place in a sprayed pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tender.

title: kraut, backbones and ribs
directions: Singe the feet to burn off all the hairs.
Cut off the toe nails with an ax. Scrape the feet well and wash several times in warm water.
Boil in water until tender. Add some salt.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan mix sugar, butter, marshmallows and milk. Place on low heat.
After mixture comes to a boil, cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into buttered dish; cut when cool.

title: virginia's gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in molasses and eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Dip one side in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
(Undercook a little if you do not want them crunchy.)

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, omitting margarine and adding 1 1/2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute mushroom caps in 2 tablespoons margarine until brown, then place in baking dish.
Cook chopped stems, red pepper and green onions in remaining margarine until tender.
Add vegetable mixture to stuffing mix, then spoon into mushroom caps.
Sprinkle mushrooms
with 1 1/2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and broil in preheated oven for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, pineapple, cream cheese and nuts in bowl. Cook vinegar, sugar and flour until thick.
Pour over salad.
Let cool 2 hours before serving.

title: betty's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread on floured surface and knead until smooth.
Pat out dough about 1-inch thick and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pan.
Spread oil on top of each biscuit and bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Store mixture in airtight container.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Empty cake mix into a large bowl.
Add pudding, oil, water, eggs, poppy seed and orange rind.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While cake is baking, make glaze by mixing confectioners sugar and lemon juice.
Turn cooled cake onto plate and drizzle glaze over top of cake.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350° grease a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.

title: orange no-bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Form dough into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Freeze.
Serve from freezer.
Refrigerate dough before rolling into balls.

title: russell's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Cook macaroni and drain off liquid.
Mix chili mix with hot water.
Add all ingredients into large pot (Dutch oven) and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer at least 15 minutes.
Better if allowed to cool, refrigerate overnight and reheated the next day.

title: sour cream pastries
directions: With pastry blender, cut oleo into flour until it resembles fine crumbs. Combine yolk and sour cream. Blend into flour mixture. Chill dough several hours. Divide into 4 equal parts, keeping each part refrigerated until ready to use. Roll each part into a 10-inch circle on lightly floured surface. Spread 2 tablespoons preserves; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons coconut and 1 tablespoon pecans.

title: tony's tasty noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Saute butter, garlic and onion. Mix into noodles with parsley, salt and pepper.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and set aside; chop onion, celery and boiled egg. Rinse rice in cold water and drain; drain corn.

Mix rice, onion, celery or pepper, mayonnaise and corn (salt and pepper to taste and garlic powder; if you use garlic salt, do not use other salt). Sprinkle top with grated cheese and put in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: banana bread
directions: At medium speed on mixer, beat shortening until creamy; add sugar.
Beat until light; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, mixing after each addition.
Stir in bananas.
Bake in loaf pan, well greased and floured, in a 350° oven.
Let cool 20 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly first 3 ingredients. Add flour and salt mixing well, then add nuts. Chill dough. Roll into 1 inch balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet, bake until set (but not brown) at 400° for 10-12 minutes. While still warm, roll in powdered sugar. Let cool, then roll in powdered sugar again. Makes 4 dozen, 1 inch cookies.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in butter until like coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and the light cream; add all at once, stirring just enough to moisten.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pan, building up edges slightly.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Split in 2 layers.
Lift top off carefully.
Butter bottom layer.
Spoon berries and the whipped cream or Cool Whip between layers and on top.

title: poppy cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine biscuit mix, cheese and poppy seed.
Add egg and milk and mix just to blend.
Beat for 1 minute. Turn into greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with additional poppy seed.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour shells
directions: Cook springers as directed on package and drain. Add pepper, onion, vinegar, oil, sugar and soup to springers.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut caramel pies
directions: Melt oleo in skillet; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown; stir frequently.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 cream cheese mix in each pie crust.
Drizzle 1/4 caramel topping on each and sprinkle 1/4 coconut mix on each.
Repeat layers. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix soda with sour cream.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: beanie weenies
directions: Place all ingredients in a microwave-safe casserole.
Mix well.
Microwave on High 6 minutes or until warm.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: quiche
directions: Put cooked, crumbled bacon in pie shell along with spinach and shredded cheese.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix flour in milk until smooth.
Add butter.
Pour over ingredients in pie shell. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimiento; mix well. Turn into a 1-quart casserole.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco mix, cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread over bottom of dish.
Layer with lettuce, tomatoes, onions, peppers and olives.
Add cheese on top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Place cheese between 2 pieces of waxed paper and use rolling pin to flatten to 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Set aside.
Blend Tabasco sauce and mustard into cream cheese.
Remove top layer of waxed paper from American cheese and spread cream cheese mixture over processed cheese.
Sprinkle bacon, onion and pimento over cheeses.
Fold longest side of cheese 2-inches over the middle with cream cheese mixture in the center.
Fold remaining third of cheese toward the middle, forming a strip 12 x 2-inches.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, cut into thin strips; arrange on serving tray.
Strips can be cut in half, if desired.
Makes about 48.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Stir together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Pat remaining mix in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, remaining eggs, cinnamon and evaporated milk together; pour over cake mixture.
Combine walnuts, sugar and reserved mixture.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts; set aside.
Cook broccoli; set aside. In baking dish mix soup (concentrated) with Miracle Whip and lemon juice.
Add broccoli (chopped) and chicken (cut into small pieces).
Top with shredded cheese and crumbled potato chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered. Serve hot.

title: substitute for powdered sugar
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in blender.
Blend on high until powdered.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash and mix other ingredients except for marshmallows.
Put in baking dish and top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° until marshmallows are light brown.

title: quick swiss quiche
directions: In blender container, combine eggs, milk, butter, biscuit mix, salt and pepper.
Blend for a few seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese, bacon, onion and herbs. Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: superfast blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish. In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour evenly over butter.
Combine berries, sugar and water.
Spoon evenly over flour mixture.
Don't stir.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: breast of chicken luau
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper towels.
Heat margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken skin side down, three pieces at a time and brown on all sides.
Remove as browned.
Saute scallions, stirring about 2 minutes.
Return chicken breasts to skillet. Sprinkle with salt, ginger and brown sugar.
Drain pineapple slices; cut slices in half and reserve liquid.
Add water to pineapple liquid to make 1 cup; add soy sauce and cornstarch to liquid.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken breasts in skillet. Add pineapple.
Bring to boiling, simmer, covered, 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken breasts are tender.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen for later use.
If frozen, bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°, covered during the first hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: To softened cream cheese, add ingredients.
Mix together.
If too thick, more catsup and mayonnaise can be added.

title: barley soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery in a Dutch oven.
Add tomato juice, water, spices and barley.
Cook over low heat for one hour.

title: carrot ring mold
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs in a large bowl; mix well and set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy and thickened.
Gently fold eggs into carrot mixture.
Spoon mixture into a well buttered 1 1/2-quart rind mold.
Bake in a preheated 350° gas oven 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool slightly.
Invert carrot ring onto serving platter.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cranberry meat loaf
directions: In large
bowl,
mix
tablespoons A.1., beef, onion, bread crumbs,
eggs, 3/4 cup cranberry sauce, salt and pepper. Pack into greased
2-quart ring mold.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Let rest 5 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil together the sugar and syrup.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
When peanut butter has melted, add corn flakes until they take up the mixture.
Drop from spoon on greased dish or greased tinfoil.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar and water to make syrup.
Add syrup with confectioners sugar; cook until stringy.
Add egg whites, vanilla and walnuts.
Cool in double boiler with cold water.
Stir until stiff.
Spoon out on waxed paper.
Can add food coloring to vary colors of candy.

title: margaret's fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add well beaten eggs. Add dry ingredients alternately with soda water, lemon juice and vanilla. Pour batter over fruit and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornstarch in saucepan and bring to a boil. Take out some of the sauce (about 1/4 cup) and mix in about 1 tablespoon cornstarch until blended.
Return cornstarch mixture to sauce in pan, blending well to thicken without lumps.
If too thin, repeat cornstarch addition.
Goes well with deep fried chicken, pork or shrimp.

title: fried rice chicken or ham
directions: Heat oil in wok; stir-fry chicken or ham 1 to 2 minutes.
Add scallions and rice.
Continue to stir-fry until rice is hot, golden color.
Add soy sauce and salt.
Make well in rice, pour in beaten egg; stir well until egg coagulates; add peas and heat. Garnish with egg omelet, cut in 1/4- inch strips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice carrots and boil in salted water until fork-tender. Rinse in ice water.
Alternate layers of carrots, bell pepper and onion in serving dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat until well blended.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate.
Keep covered.
(May be drained before serving.)

title: thanksgiving waldorf salad
directions: Place first four ingredients in salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour over fruit.
Toss lightly.
Serve in lettuce lined salad bowls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Mix dough and allow to rise 2 hours.
Divide into 3 parts because you will be making 3 strombolis.
After dough has risen, spread dough out onto a greased counter into a large oval.
Spread thin layer of mustard on dough.
Next, spread a thin layer of barbecue sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano, black pepper and garlic salt.
Down center of dough, put a row of ham slices over salami, onions and peppers.
Over that, put a generous portion of grated cheeses all mixed together.
Bring sides of dough up over top and secure with skewers or toothpicks.
Spread butter or oil over top and sprinkle with black pepper and oregano.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice down and eat with fingers.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Grease	a
10-inch
baking dish.
Arrange
broccoli
in dish. In small bowl of electric mixer, beat
egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold in remaining
ingredients;
spoon over broccoli. Broil 3
inches
from
unit
in electric oven for 3 minutes, or until meringue is golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peking pork pasta salad
directions: In a large frying pan, heat cooking oil to medium high temperature.
Add pork; stir-fry quickly.
Remove pork from pan and place in a large bowl.
Combine soy sauce, sherry and sesame oil.
Pour half over pork strips; toss well.
Cover and marinate 1 hour.
Toss pasta, green onion and green pepper with remaining soy sauce mixture.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Arrange pasta mixture on spinach leaves.
Top with pork; garnish with almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot oil. Place chicken, onion and cheese in each tortilla and roll and place in baking dish. In saucepan, melt butter and add flour. Stir until well blended. Slowly, add chicken broth and cook until mixture thickens. Stir in sour cream and peppers; do not boil. Pour over tortillas. Bake 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Slice your ice cream in 1/2-inch slices.
Put between 2 graham crackers and eat.
Real good.

title: colorado peach cream pie
directions: Cut butter into flour and salt.
Press into 9-inch pie pan. Slice peaches; sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand while preparing rest of filling.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl and serve.

title: carrot-cheese bake
directions: Combine rice, carrots, 1 1/2 cups cheese, milk, eggs, onions and seasonings.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and salt in a large bowl.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Add sugar and vinegar (do not heat). Mix well until sugar is dissolved.
Pack in plastic containers. Cover and put in freezer.

title: beefy mexican casserole
directions: Combine corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in large bowl.
Mix and set aside.
Brown meat, drain and set aside.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon corn meal in well greased 12-inch iron skillet.
Pour 1/2 of meal mixture.
Sprinkle evenly with beef, then onion, then cheese and peppers last.
Pour remaining batter evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Cook broccoli in water.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cream of mushroom soup to onion when it is golden brown.
Add mushrooms and juice.
Break up garlic cheese and add to mixture.
Add broccoli (drained) and Tabasco and mix well.
Serve hot with crackers, chips, French bread or whatever.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute margarine with onion, celery and garlic.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Add water and simmer for 2 hours.
Add 1/2 pound ham shank, if desired.

title: louise's cherry coke salad
directions: Drain
cherries
and
pineapple;
reserve
juice.
Heat juice and
dissolve jello.
Add cola, cherries, pineapple and nuts. Grate frozen cream cheese on top and let salad congeal. Use large pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: doug's mexican cornbread
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 375° oven until top browns and begins to crack (25 to 45 minutes).
Makes 1 large or 2 medium pans of bread.
The hit of any meal!

title: vegetable dip or salad dressing
directions: Mix all together and put in jars with tops.
Keep in refrigerator.
This will be good for 3 or 4 months.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt oleo over low heat.
Stir in seasonings.
Add ingredients and mix well.
Heat at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix with pastry blender flour, sugar, baking powder and egg. Sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: out of this world fudge
directions: Stir sugar and milk together in a large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Makes a broiler pan full.

title: potato salad(heritage recipe)
directions: Mash the potatoes, add 1 stick oleo and salt, pepper, and celery seed. Mix well.

title: corn souffle
directions: Beat together eggs and oil; add muffin mix and corn.
Bake in casserole or souffle bowl for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: renegade chili
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef and onions; drain off grease.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat 3 eggs. Combine sugar, nutmeg, vanilla, and milk. Mix in rice and raisins. Bake in oven for one hour and fifteen minutes at 350 degrees in a large casserole.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch and water to a boil.
Add jello and cool.
Arrange whole or sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Pour filling over strawberries.
Keep in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: carol's coconut cake
directions: This cake is so easy you don't even need a recipe.
Bake white cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions. Poke holes in top of cake as soon as you take it from the oven and pour sweetened condensed milk over all.
Cool completely.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle all over with coconut.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Put potatoes, carrots, beans, peas and beets into separate bowls.
Pour salad dressing over each vegetable; chill thoroughly.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Clean crabmeat.
Place in large bowl and set aside.
In small bowl, mix mayo, egg, milk, Worcestershire, mustard, celery salt, pepper, paprika and ginger.
Pour sauce over crabmeat and mix gently, but thoroughly.
Carefully mix in bread crumbs.
Place shrimp in baking pan and heap with crab mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until crab mixture begins to brown.
Mix mayo, egg, Old Bay and Tabasco.
Spread a generous amount over each shrimp.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken and rice(one dish)
directions: In large baking dish, sprayed with Pam, add rice and water. Stir to mix.
Add onion, bell peppers, mushrooms, carrots (if desired), cream of mushroom soup and chicken breasts.
Cover with foil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and brown chicken for 20 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Crush crackers.
Combine with oleo.
Press into 1 9-inch pie pan.
Put green beans on top of crackers.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: our lord's scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together to create this divine fruit cake.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: butter-and-herb rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt in a saucepan. Place over low heat, stirring until shortening melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Stir into yeast mixture.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend together; place in greased casserole.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not use mixer.
Blend well and pour in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While cake is warm, pour icing over cake.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Combine apples and water in 2-quart microwave-safe dish. Microwave, covered, on full power, 9 to 11 minutes or until soft. Stir once or twice.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with 1 chopped onion and garlic; add tomato sauce, juice, green chili (optional) and spices.
Place a layer of tortilla chips on bottom of large greased casserole.
Cover with layer of meat mixture and 1 can beans.
Repeat, ending with a third layer of tortilla chips.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover for the last 15 minutes.
Cover the top with a thick layer of lettuce, remaining onion, fresh tomatoes and grated cheese just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in Pyrex dish.
Top with potato chips, crushed.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: waldorf salad(serves 6)
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and walnuts.
Add enough dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add additional dressing and garnish with apple slices before serving.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place carrots, onions and celery in crock-pot. Add chicken, chicken broth, water, brown gravy mix and seasonings. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: In a
large
saucepan saute onion, garlic and celery in butter, stirring
for 5 minutes.
Add remaining sauce ingredients; mix well.
Bring
to
a
boil, stirring; reduce heat and simmer (covered),	stirring
occasionally.
Cook
for about 2 hours.

title: special toast topping
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on toast.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook beef, garlic and onion until beef is browned, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat until boiling; reduce heat to low.
Add steamed or microwaved broccoli.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Fast and easy. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
20 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour barbecued chicken
directions: Sprinkle chickens on all sides with salt and pepper.
In a skillet, heat oil and saute onion until golden.
Stir in catsup, peach preserves, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and salt.
Stir to blend well; remove from heat.
Place pieces of chicken into a shallow roasting pan in a single layer, bony side up.
Brush chicken with sauce, heavily, and turn, skin side up. Brush chicken with remaining sauce.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until chicken is tender and well glazed.
Serves 8.

title: crunchy cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter in bowl until soft.
Add grated cheese, salt, cayenne, sifted flour and cornflakes.
Combine beaten egg and milk (reserve 2 teaspoons for glazing).
Add remaining milk to cornflake mixture and mix thoroughly.
Roll teaspoonfuls of mixture into balls.
Put on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Press top lightly with a fork.
Brush top with egg and milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grilled chicken tacos
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook onion and garlic until tender. Add chicken; heat 3 minutes.
Remove from pan into bowl.
Heat tortillas according to package directions.
Divide chicken onto center of tortillas; top with cheese and optional ingredients, if desired.
Fold tortillas in half.
Melt margarine in same skillet. Grill tacos on each side for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: mango cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; beat together well. Chop mangos and add to mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients together and then mix with mango mixture.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: *This is a blend that they are all in one package.

title: lemon barbecue chicken
directions: Place drumsticks in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake vigorously.
Pour 2 cups over drumsticks; reserve and refrigerate remaining 1/2 cup mixture.
Seal bag and refrigerate 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade, discarding marinade.
Cook, covered with grill lid, over medium coals (300° to 350°) 15 minutes on each side, basting occasionally with reserved marinade.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit wine
directions: You will also need a gallon jar, airlock and cork to fit jar, 2 or 3 gallon plastic container and plastic tubing.

title: caponata
directions: Saute pine nuts in olive oil and drain.
Then continue on with recipe.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Preheat oven per directions on crescent roll can.
Take one piece of triangular roll, lay flat on cookie sheet.
Stuff approximately one teaspoonful of sausage and roll up.
Bake until all sides are browned.
Keep flipping.

title: southern style baked corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour and salt; add eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch buttered baking dish.
You may sprinkle with a little nutmeg and cinnamon, if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until corn is a golden brown.
Also dot with butter before baking.

title: "buckeyes"(candy)
directions: Melt margarine. Mix in peanut butter and sugar. Form into 3/4-inch balls. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate delight bites
directions: *Or use 1 tablespoon almond, coffee or orange liqueur.

title: my favorite salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup hot water.
Combine all ingredients and add to jello.
Chill until firm.

title: the adams family french baked potatoes
directions: Clean the potatoes. Slice them lengthwise (thick or thin, as you like them). Line the potato slices together in rows on cookie sheet (with lip, so butter does not drip in oven). Spread or squirt butter over all potatoes, then sprinkle with garlic salt, paprika and pepper, as desired.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until completely baked (depending on how many and how thick of potatoes you use).
Serve when finished.
They're delicious.

title: "double good" macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed and drain. Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl and mix until blended. Fold in macaroni.
Put in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: calico cauliflower salad
directions: Wash, dice and cut up all vegetables into bite size pieces. Place in a large covered bowl.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over vegetables and stir.
Pour the entire bottle of dressing over the mixture and blend well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, stir to coat vegetables.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in molasses.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: tortilla roll up
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together.
Spread on tortilla. Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Slice and serve with salsa.
(Can be frozen.)

title: pecan fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla & salt over low heat until smooth, stirring occasionally.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture into a buttered 9x5 inch loaf pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: buffet vegetable bake
directions: Cook frozen vegetables using package directions until tender-crisp; drain.
Add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients except crumbs in bowl; mix well.
Add to vegetables; toss to mix.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Makes 1 gallon.
Pour water into a large stock pot and bring to a boil.
Add celery, onions, carrots and chicken base; simmer for 30 minutes.
Melt margarine over low heat in a large skillet; add flour and mix constantly until smooth.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes without scorching.
Add roux to soup and continue to stir until smooth and thick.
Add Cheez Whiz and grated cheese until cheese is melted.
Add heated milk to soup (add additional milk if soup is too thick).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees until firm.

title: the impeccable pig's vanilla rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and beaten egg.
Add vanilla.
Place shortening in bread bowl.
Pour yeast mixture over and mix with spoon.
Gradually add flour, 1 cup at a time and mix until somewhat sticky dough is formed.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Roll out to 1/4-inch.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place in baking sheet.
Pat with melted butter and fold in half. Pinch closed.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: michigan picante sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and puree for 10 to 15 seconds.

title: mac's 5-alarm chili
directions: In a cast-iron pan, brown meat with onions and peppers.
Add beans, tomatoes and water.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 3 hours. Add liquid, if needed, to keep it from burning.
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Cool.
Let ripen in refrigerator overnight.
Skim off fat.
Reheat to serve, with cole slaw, orange juice, crackers and cherry pie.

title: white pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites
and
set
aside.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until real soft
and	light.	Add
some
of
the egg whites and some of the flour that has been sifted three times. Continue to add egg	whites	and flour, alternately with juice or
citrus punch.
Add
flavoring;
continue
to
mix.
Scrape sides of bowl and mix well.
Pour mixture into a tube pan that has been greased and floured
with
waxed paper in the bottom. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french toast(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: In a small bowl, combine Egg Beaters, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
In nonstick skillet over medium heat, melt 2 teaspoons margarine.
Dip bread slices in Egg Beater mixture to coat. Transfer to skillet. Brown about 3 minutes on each side, adding remaining margarine to skillet as needed. Serve with syrup, if desired.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl mix baking powder, salt, 3 cups flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Reserve 1 tablespoon corn-oil spread for crumb topping.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in remaining corn-oil spread until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk, vanilla extract and egg until flour is just moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries; spoon batter into loaf pans.
Coarsely chop almonds.
In small bowl, with fork, mix almonds, 2 tablespoons cake flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and reserved corn-oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle crumb topping over batter.
Bake loaf 1 hour and 20 minutes; remove from pans and finish cooling on wire rack.

title: cherry chicken
directions: Split and remove skin from chicken breasts.
Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine pie filling with lemon juice, salt and ginger.
Pour filling over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
This is a very glamorous dish!
Serve chicken on hot rice. Spoon mixture over chicken.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan with Pam.
Layer Bundt pan as follows:
walnut pieces (pecans), pudding, brown sugar, cinnamon, yeast rolls and butter.
Put in oven overnight.
Lower the top rack in the oven. Bake in the morning at 350° for 25 minutes.
Invert pan onto plate. Let it set for a few minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Spread on bread slices on baking sheet.
Broil until melts.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and vanilla; add powdered sugar and salt.
Gradually add flour, then nuts.
Mix until mixture holds together and is stiff.
Roll into balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes until set but not brown.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Wait a few minutes and roll again.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place ladyfingers around the sides and on the bottom of a greased 9 inch spring-form pan.
Pour filling into pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Remove sides of pan.
Top with strawberries.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook and drain linguini; dry on clean towel to remove excess water. Combine with as many raw vegetables as you wish, seasoning and dressing; toss well.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Blend chicken soup and water until dissolved.
Add egg and beat.
Using Teflon skillet, rub with oil and heat skillet on medium.
Pour in egg mixture and add pepper.
Stir.
Take skillet off heat just before desired thickness and stir.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt oleo with peanut butter; cool.
Slowly beat in sugar and vanilla.

title: parmesan walleye
directions: Place filets in a buttered dish in a single layer.
Brush with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients in a small bowl.
Broil filets 3 to 4-inches from the burner for 5 minutes and then turn.
Spread remaining mixture on top and broil for another 3 to 4 minutes.
Watch Parmesan cheese carefully to avoid burning.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Cook vegetables together until soft (20 to 30 minutes). Put through a colander and then
through
a fine sieve or food mill. Add sugar and salt to juice; heat to boiling.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on a bun.

title: western skillet noodles
directions: In a medium skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Add water and bring to boil.
Stir in noodles and beef flavored sauce.
Add chili powder.
Continue to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 7 minutes.
Add corn and 2/3 cup cheese.
Simmer 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining cheese and serve.

title: four-layer chocolate dessert
directions: Blend and bake like pie crust in a long glass baking dish at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked brie 1
directions: Microwave butter and brown sugar in glass measuring cup until butter is melted. Mix thoroughly. Drizzle over brie so it runs down the sides. Sprinkle with sliced almonds. Bake 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until brie is soft and almonds are toasted. Enjoy on crusty bread
rounds.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Mix all together.
Better if made and refrigerated for a few hours before served.

title: candied yams(no fail)
directions: Pour all into a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to medium. Continue boiling until liquid is thick; never stir.
Shake pot a little to mix the ingredients in the beginning.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: In a heavy sauce pan combine marshmallow, sugar, evaporated milk, oleo and salt, stirring steady bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butterscotch morsels, orange extract and orange rind.
Stir until smooth and add nuts then pour into 8 x 8 inch pan.

title: cream cheese pie with fruit glaze
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and beat until smooth.
Pour into pie crust
and
bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until set. Chill. Drain fruit cocktail or any other fruit and arrange on top. Canned
cherry
pie filling may be spread on top instead of fruit.

title: tasty cheese wafers
directions: Let butter and cheese come to room temperature.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Shape into two or three rolls of 1-inch diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill. Slice roll into 1/4-inch thick slices and bake on ungreased sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well and keep in refrigerator. Use on fresh spinach or lettuce salad.

title: stuffed italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together the first eight ingredients.
On waxed paper, pat meat mixture into a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat mixture, leaving a small margin around the edges. Place Mozzarella cheese slices on top of ham.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix mango, onion, pizza topping, garlic, salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce. Let simmer.
Cook spaghetti noodles; drain.

title: world's best chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake together. Pour into greased and floured 17 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: violet meringues
directions: Line a cookie sheet with nonstick baking paper. Put egg whites in a large grease free bowl. Whisk them until they form stiff peaks. Whisk in one tablespoon at a time the sugar. Fold in candied violets and food coloring. Use 2 tablespoons to shape the mixture into little ovals on the lined cookie sheet.

title: mom's casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage.
Drain, then add onion, garlic, celery, green pepper, salt, pepper and oleo. Cook.
Cook noodles. Drain and set aside.
Add to meat mixture the tomato soup, Hunt's sauce, macaroni sauce, mushrooms, black olives and Cheez Whiz. Mix in noodles and put in a large pan.
Sprinkle a generous amount of grated cheese on top.
Top off with 2 cups Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
If needed, add a little water while baking.

title: cockeyed chocolate cake(makes 9 servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water. Stir until flour disappears.
Pour into a lightly greased or nonstick 9 x 9-inch square pan; bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maple fudge
directions: Mix together in a heavy 2-quart saucepan, sugar, butter, evaporated milk, milk and 2 tablespoons maple syrup.
Bring to a boil quickly, stirring continuously.
Reduce to medium heat when bubbles appear; cook and stir for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Creme, remaining maple syrup and walnuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan; cool thoroughly.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: one-eye bandits
directions: Cut a hole in the center of the slice of bread, using a small cup or with a knife.
Heat a frying pan over medium fire, melting butter in the pan.

title: aunt betty's toffee
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Line cookie pan with saltine crackers, fit them closely together. Microwave on high approximately 4 minutes, the butter and brown sugar. Pour mixture over crackers slowly to allow crackers to absorb the mixture. Bake 350° for 15-20 minutes. Take out of oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers and spread as they melt. Sprinkle pecans over chocolate allow to cool completely. Break into pieces and serve.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients, thicken with cornstarch and cold water.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans, wash and drain kidney beans.
Mix first seven ingredients.
Combine rest of ingredients to make the dressing. Add dressing to the bean mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Mix lightly now and then; better if prepared the day before using.
Will keep well for 1 week or more.
Good to the last bean.

title: baked corn
directions: Whip first 4 ingredients then add remaining.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crush-catchin marshmallow nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Stir peanut butter chips into prepared brownie batter. Grease an 8 x 13-inch baking dish with softened butter and line with foil. Pour in the brownie batter and spread into an even layer. Sprinkle the top with chopped nuts and bake 20 to 22 minutes. Top with marshmallows in the last 3 minutes of baking. Remove from oven. Allow to cool and cut into 12 brownies.

title: best barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket on heavy-duty foil.
Mix remaining ingredients (except barbecue sauce) together and brush on brisket.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in foil for 4 hours in a 300° oven.
Open foil and pour on barbecue sauce.
Bake for 1 more hour or until done.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Slice across grain of meat.

title: sesame salmon with ginger-butter garnish
directions: Pour sesame seeds onto a plate and dredge the salmon until completely coated on all sides.
Push the seeds firmly into fish so they adhere during the cooking process.
Heat sesame oil until just about to smoke.
Add fish and fry fast and hot, until golden brown on all sides.
Stir ginger into softened butter.
When fish is done, spoon a dollop of ginger-butter on top and serve immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in pie crust at 300 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat half the sugar with shortening and butter.
Gradually add milk.
Continue beating; add extract and gradually add remaining sugar until the right consistency is reached.
Yield:
Frosting for 24 cupcakes.

title: debbie's sugar cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, then oil and then vanilla. Sift the dry ingredients and add to rest.
Chill.
Form into balls and press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: sweetheart tarts
directions: Line muffin tins with pastry.
Put 1 teaspoon of your favorite jam in bottom.
Fill with the following.
Mix coconut, egg, milk, sugar, salt and almond flavoring together.
Spoon into unbaked pastry shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes and line bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole. Sprinkle a layer of browned sausage and then layer shredded cheese. Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper and pour over top of other ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, confectioners sugar, 1 cup pecans and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll half in sugar and remainder in 1/2 cup nuts.

title: magnolia sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1 cup of sugar until forms stiff peaks; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Add 1 cup of sugar and beat.
Add hot milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in meringue mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serve unfrosted.

title: peach pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add nearly 1/2 cup of milk and stir.
Melt margarine; mix together with peaches and vanilla in a 9-inch baking pan.
Pour flour mixture over top.
Sprinkle top generously with sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cauliflower - broccoli toss
directions: Mix salad dressing mix with mayonnaise and milk.
Mix together all vegetables, sugar, cheese and salt.
Add dressing.

title: miss lillian russell's asparagus souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into greased baking dish.
Cook about 35 or 45 minutes in slow oven.
Can be prepared in advance.

title: aunt be be's sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes whole with a pinch of salt.
Add butter to potatoes while still hot.
Separate eggs.
Put egg whites aside. Add the rest of the ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into pie mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in carrots, zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 350° until center springs back when touched.
(A moist cake.)

title: eggplant and sausage casserole
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut sausage diagonally into 1-inch wide pieces.
In a large skillet or heavy saucepan, heat oil over moderately high heat.
Add sausage and cook for 8 minutes or until sausage is browned, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon.

title: irma's salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add cream cheese to dissolve.
Add cold water, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Chill until partly congealed.
Whip with whisk and fold in celery and onion.
Return to refrigerator to reset.
Makes 6 small molds.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook diced potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain off water and add the remaining ingredients while potatoes are still hot.
Mix well.

title: jam cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Blend in flour.
Shape into ball; cover and chill.
Roll very thin on floured board.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Place 1/4 teaspoon jam in center.
Moisten edges with water; fold in half.
Press edges with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Coat with sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, rice, salt and pepper.
Roll into balls.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Add tomato sauce and water in a separate pot.
