Add meatballs to sauce and cook slow for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fast fixin' chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a large glass bowl.
Add milk and butter; do not stir.
Cook at High for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes in microwave until butter is melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Spread into well-greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: strivley's(called funnel cakes at fair.)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup milk, until there are no lumps.
Add milk.
Put 1 inch of oil in frying pan.
Heat oil. Put batter (less than 1/2 cup at a time) into a funnel.
Starting in center of pan, make a continuous coil until funnel is empty. Cook for about 3 minutes.
Turn over and cook the second side about 2 minutes.
Serve with syrup or powdered sugar.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add to the rest of ingredients and bring to a boil, then let simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: good beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Cook on top of stove until warmed.

title: deer roast
directions: Rub meat with vinegar, then sprinkle with salt and peppers. Put in roaster pan.
Put the two slices of bacon, bay leaves and Italian dressing over the roast.
Cut up all the vegetables.
Cook roast, covered, in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Then add all cut up vegetables.
Continue to cook, covered, until roast and vegetables are tender.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs until even.
Mix in milk and creamed corn.
Break crackers into crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rises.

title: mud pie
directions: Take filling out of Oreo cookies.
Crush cookies and stir with melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of pie pan.
Chill in refrigerator about 1/2 hour.
Fill crust with toffee ice cream and freeze.
Pour layer of caramel fudge topping on ice cream and return to freezer for another 15 minutes.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with plenty of sliced almonds.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn on to a surface big enough to hold the cake.
While still hot, punch 12 holes in cake with a plastic straw.
Pour cream of coconut in the holes until all is absorbed.
Let cake completely cool before putting Cool Whip and coconut on cake.
Keep in refrigerator until going to serve.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch or 9-inch) round pans.
Sift flour and cocoa three times.
This is a must. Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to buttermilk mixture; add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour evenly into cake pans and bake for 28 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick comes clean from center.
Cool completely.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Put in baking dish with slivered almonds on top.
Heat under broiler just until warm.
Nice served in dish with candle warmer.

title: hawaiian poo poo
directions: Mix together and spread on small platter the cream cheese, curry powder, mayonnaise and milk.
Sprinkle on cheese mixture in this order the olives, shrimp and hard-boiled eggs.
Serve on crackers.

title: joanne's blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss berries with lemon and sugar; place in a deep dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix or work by hand until the mixture looks glossy or shiny. Pat out on wax paper to 1-inch thickness.
Chill and cut.

title: apple-cinnamon dog biscuits(dog treats)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Stir together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the applesauce and egg, and blend thoroughly.
Then add the water gradually, stirring with a wooden spoon.
The dough should be very stiff; if not, add a little more flour.
Knead the dough with your hands to create a smooth texture.
Roll the dough 1/4 inch thick.
(It helps if the "top" and "bottom" of the dough are lightly floured.)
Use a cookie cutter to cut out the biscuits.
Place the biscuits about 1/2 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for about 38 to 50 minutes.
The biscuits should be lightly browned on the outside and they should not be moist inside.
Turn the oven off and let the biscuits stay inside without opening the oven door for five hours or overnight to let them harden.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes four dozen 3-inch-long by 1-inch-wide biscuits.

title: yellow squash croquette
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of water until tender, drain and mash.
Add bread crumbs and next 5 ingredients.
Add more bread crumbs if mixture is too soft.
Shape mixture into small logs and roll in cornmeal.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: burnt creme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around the edge.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick, about 3 minutes.
Gradually beat cream into egg yolks. Stir in vanilla and pour into 6 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Place cups in baking dish with 1/2-inch water in the bottom.
Bake until set, about 45 minutes.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Sprinkle each cup with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Place on top rack under broiler. Cook until topping is medium brown.
Chill before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream with mixer; spread in long casserole dish. Cover with lettuce. Layer with onions. Spread next layer of tomatoes, green olives and black olives. Then cover with taco sauce. Sprinkle with cheese and refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham crackers and melted oleo.
Press in bottom of loaf pan.
Mix the eggs, powdered sugar and soft oleo.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust. Cover with the diced bananas. Spread the crushed pineapple over the bananas. Spread the Cool Whip over the bananas. Garnish with walnuts and
cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion together; drain.
Mix 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 bag Tater Tots with all other ingredients; mix well.
Put the rest of the Tater Tots on top.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Stir all together.
Add flour last, sprinkle little at a time. Let rise until double.
Roll out like biscuits.
Cut with cutter. Put a piece of butter in center of each one, then turn over halfway and put together.
Let rise and bake in oven at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry pink cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl and beat vigorously for 2 minutes to get color even.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) layer cake pans that have been greased and lined with waxed paper in the bottom.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma's pumpkin bread(makes 2 large or 6 small loaves)
directions: Also, add cloves to liking, pumpkin seasoning and allspice to taste.
Nuts are optional.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternately add flour, baking powder and salt with milk. Add flavorings.
Pour in a greased and floured tube cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt butter
and chocolate. Add butter flavoring and chopped nuts. Mix flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine two mixes with a spoon. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
In small mixing bowl, mix together the cream cheese, milk and bacon bits.
Put 1/2 teaspoon mixture in each mushroom.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave vanilla mints
directions: Melt bark or coating on High power 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir.
If not melted, continue to cook until melted well.
Stir in peppermint candy.
Pour onto waxed paper or cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Melt shortening in skillet over medium heat.
Cook the onions in the shortening for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Cook meat until brown. Add the soup, catsup, salt and pepper.
Stir well and cook until it is bubbling all over.
Serve on hamburg buns.
Serves 4.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt paraffin, peanut butter and chips.
Add peanuts and stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon on foil, let set until hardened.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Blend Jell-O, cream cheese, sugar and hot water in blender. Chill mixture until it begins to thicken.
Add pineapple and orange sections; fold in whipped topping.
Pour into mold or rectangular dish; chill until congealed.
(Use a 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 smaller dishes.
This recipe makes a lot!)

title: caramel corn party
directions: Boil brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Mix with popcorn and bake at 200° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cream margarine and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake until golden brown.

title: round steak special
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt, pepper and flour; pound on both sides with meat pounder or edge of heavy saucer.
In a large, heavy skillet or Dutch oven, brown steak well in a few tablespoons of hot fat.
Top with sliced onions.
Combine tomato sauce with rest of ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Watch carefully to prevent sticking.
Add water as tomato sauce cooks away.
Serves 4.

title: edna's see's fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk together for 8 minutes (start count after comes to a rolling boil).
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, margarine, vanilla and salt. Stir until thick.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into large buttered cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour, then cut into squares.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, salt, pepper, egg, flour and baking powder until very smooth.
Potatoes can be done in a food processor.
Once the batter is mixed, heat a frypan with shortening.
When the shortening or oil is hot, take a large tablespoon and drop the batter in the oil.
(Be careful you don't let the oil splatter on you and you get burned.)
Once you put the batter in the pan spread it some with the spoon.
Once it is brown on one side turn and brown the other side.
Place on a paper towel to drain a little. You can eat them just with salt or with applesauce and sour cream on the side.
These are what Great-Grandma used to make for us when we were growning up.
You can use only 3 potatoes since you are only 2 people.
But they are so good you'll eat them up.

title: ice cream topping
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa mix. Add can of milk. Let come to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add poppy seed.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "recipe for life"
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add Tears of Joy, Sorrow and Sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of Prayer and Faith to lighten the other ingredients.
After pouring all of this into your Family Life, bake well with the Heat of Human Kindness.
Serve with a Smile.

title: roberto's garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on French bread.
Wrap bread with foil and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and broil until golden.

title: garden ratatouille
directions: Lightly butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole with a lid. Put in all vegetables in any order. Sprinkle with basil, cumin and garlic. Drizzle with olive oil. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°, depending on how well done you like vegetables.
Cover vegetables with cheese slices and bake additional 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, then add the other ingredients.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Use lots of flour to roll out dough.
Cut shapes.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: autumn punch
directions: Perk in a large percolator.
Makes 2 gallons. Garnish with a cinnamon stick or orange slice. Serve hot.

title: cornbread pudding
directions: Mix everything except cheese.
Pour in shallow baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Put cheese on top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: clam balls
directions: Saute onion and Celery in oleo.
Put all ingredients into large bowl and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed potato chips and sprinkle 1/2 cup fancy grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy Kisses, in large mixer bowl.
Mix on low speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Roll balls in white sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy Kiss; press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs (2 at a time and beat well), syrup, flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk, onion and egg together very well.
Add ground beef, etc.
Shape into balls and place on a cookie sheet (with sides).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until brown.
(You may want to turn once.)

title: nut bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add flour and baking soda last.
Allow to rise 15 minutes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° in 2 greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, butter and lemon juice.
Grate rind and add last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13 dish with rolls.
Combine milk, eggs and salt; mix well and pour over rolls.
Add drained sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes then add the grated cheese.
Let it melt on the top.
If you like more cheese, put some in the mix of milk and eggs.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soups, vegetables (thawed) and chicken. Place in a 9-inch pie plate. Mix mix, egg and baking mix. Pour over the chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onion, cheese and melted butter in a bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: loaf bread or rolls
directions: Put sugar and salt in a small bowl.
Add scalded milk and oil to sugar and salt.
Add yeast to warm water.
Add beaten egg, flour and milk mixture.
Mix real good in large bowl.
Let rise until doubled, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Make into rolls or loaf bread.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple grapefruit swirls
directions: In a metal tray, stir together 1 cup of the grapefruit juice and the sugar until the sugar is dissolved; fit the tray with the divider and freeze the mixture until it is frozen solid.
In another metal ice tray fitted with the divider, pour 1 cup of the pineapple juice and freeze it until it is frozen solid.

(The fruit mixtures may be prepared up to this point 1 day in advance.) In a blender, blend the frozen grapefruit juice mixture with 1 1/2 ounces of tequila and the remaining 1/4 cup grapefruit juice, scraping down the sides occasionally, until the mixture is smooth but still frozen and divide the mixture between 2 stemmed glasses. In the cleaned blender, blend the frozen pineapple juice with the remaining 1 1/2 ounces tequila and the remaining 1/4 cup pineapple juice, scraping down the sides occasionally, until the mixture is smooth but still frozen.
Pour over grapefruit mixture.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and boil until it reaches soft ball stage. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop onto foil or wax paper.

title: angel icing
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Boil sugar, syrup and water to the hard ball stage.
Add vanilla and pour over egg whites.
Beat until of spreading consistency.
In case you should fail to cook the syrup to the right stage, a small amount of sifted powdered sugar added to the mixture will help.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until done.
Add spaghetti, soups, water, mushrooms, salt and garlic salt.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fill crust and chill at least 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip and chopped nuts or shaved chocolate.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Melt butter; add and beat vigorously.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheesy cauliflower and carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook carrots for 10 minutes.
Add cauliflower; cook for 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain; turn into casserole dish.
Saute onion and green pepper in 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk over low heat until thickened.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce until cheese melts.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt chips with salt and condensed milk.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Beat in marshmallow cream.
Quickly spread evenly into wax paper lined 11-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut in squares.
Makes about 4 pounds.
May be frozen in airtight container.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 square pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until heated through.
Uncooked mixture freezes well.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Spoon Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and oregano over chicken breasts and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Place meat in buttered casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top of meat.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of cream of mushroom soup.
Top with hash browns.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini souffle(delicious!)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease a souffle pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, about 45 minutes, or until golden on top.
Cut into squares and serve.
Great side dish!

title: ham and cheese loaf
directions: Sprinkle 1 envelope Knox unflavored gelatine on cold water to soften.
Add very hot water and stir until gelatine is thoroughly dissolved.
Add vinegar and salt.
Chill to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in diced, cooked ham, grated process American cheese, diced celery and diced sweet pickle.
Turn into a 3-cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens and serve with salad dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange ginger dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs to milk and let stand for a few minutes.
Mix with ground beef, egg, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Shape into loaf and put in baking pan. Combine catsup, brown sugar, mustard, salt and water and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients; add to other ingredients and stir until smooth.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lois' strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together thoroughly. Spread 1/2 of the cheese and sugar mixture over the bottom of the prepared pie crust.
Set remaining cheese and sugar mixture aside. In a saucepan, mix flour and sugar together.
Add water and whisk until mixed thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Add strawberry Jell-O and remove from heat.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour into pie crust and place in refrigerator.
Once the pie has set, spread the remaining 1/2 of the cheese and sugar mixture over the top.
Cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat egg, salad oil, sugar, pineapple and water.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda together.
Add to first mixture.
Add grated carrots and vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 350° oven until done.
Good iced with cream cheese frosting.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over pecans.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo.
Drop by spoonfuls on cake batter.
Do not spread to outer edges of cake, so cake can bake and seal around filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and turn into greased casserole.
Top with strips of American cheese or grated Parmesan, crushed potato chips and sprinkle with paprika for color.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Mix together; make 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes (until light brown).

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup of cake mix.
Mix together remaining cake mix with 1 egg and 1 stick oleo (melted).
Combine pumpkin, 2 eggs, milk and pumpkin spice.
Combine with first mixture.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 cup cake mix, add remaining ingredients.
Put on top of pumpkin batter and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix shortening (if vegetable shortening is used, add 2 tablespoons hot water) and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to shortening mixture, a small amount at a time.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla wafers.
Place 1 vanilla wafer into cupcake paper in cupcake tin.
Fill 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and top with favorite pie filling such as cherry or blueberry.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: stir-fry summer vegetables
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add zucchini and squash and stir 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, bean sprouts and water chestnuts; cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle soy sauce and garlic powder.
Toss thoroughly.
Serve while hot.

title: chicken breasts in brandy with cream
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper to taste.
In a skillet, saute chicken quickly in butter until meat is browned on all sides.
Remove from heat.
Pour warmed brandy over chicken. Using a long wooden match to flambe, or set fire to chicken.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix flour and Crisco.
Stir in milk to make a soft dough. Chill.
Bring to boil white sugar, water, vanilla and butter. Roll chilled dough in rectangle and sprinkle apples, brown sugar and cinnamon over it.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut in 1-inch slices.
Place slices over heated mixture in large pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Roll up in a ball.
Let stand in refrigerator 1 hour or longer.
Chop nuts up into fine pieces.
Take cheese ball and roll in nuts.
Have crackers of your choice, and you are ready.

title: ground meat and cabbage casserole
directions: Rinse cabbage and tear into pieces. Set aside to drain. Saute the meat, onion and garlic in olive oil. Drain off any grease. Add tomato sauce, salt, thyme and pepper. Stir to blend. In a casserole sprayed with PAM, place half of the cabbage and then half of the meat sauce. Repeat the layers and then top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy stromboli
directions: Unroll pizza dough into a 10 by 14-inch rectangle.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle on to dough leaving a 1-inch border on all sides.
Roll up jelly roll style and pinch the edges and seam to seal.
Bake at 400 degrees for 35 minutes.
Slice and serve!

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: Mix together.
Reserve some crumbs for top.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: just wonderful meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into well-greased large loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almost candy bars
directions: Mix cake mix with softened oleo until dark and crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread remaining ingredients except milk onto the mixture.
Pour the milk over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, then cut into bars and serve.

title: polvorones(cinnamon cakes)
directions: Cut the sugar into the lard; add the eggs and beat well.
Sift the flour with the baking powder; mix well.
Form into balls; flatten with the fingers
and sprinkle with sugar and powdered cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for cookies (3 to 4-inch diameter) or 15 minutes for smaller ones.
The big ones are more traditional.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Remove any beans that do not look good.
Then cook until soft pinch, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not drain.
Use this water to bake beans with.
If too much, save as you may need to add more liquid during baking.

title: cornbread deluxe
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating thoroughly, as you go.
Turn batter into greased 9-inch pan or for a better crust, use an iron skillet or corn stick pan.
Grease pan with drippings.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: hot creamed crab
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, flour and pepper.
Beat again until smooth. Fold in crabmeat, almonds and salt to taste.
Turn into casserole dish, cover and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Place over heat (candle or heating device) or turn into chafing dish and keep warm until serving time.
Serve with unsalted crackers or plain Melba toast.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cool jello salad
directions: Mix the lemon and lime jello together.
Pour in boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise, pineapple and juice; stir until smooth.
Pour into casserole dish; let set until firm.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Beat egg and add sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add vinegar and water or milk.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until brown.
Take bacon from fat and reserve for garnish.
Boil dressing in fat until thick and mix with lettuce. A hard-boiled egg may be sliced on top with the bacon.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with milk.
Add pudding, peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Put into baked pie shell and refrigerate overnight.

title: dilled cracker snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers. Put crackers into large bowl. Pour mixture over crackers and mix well. Store in airtight container.

title: sour cream orange cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vanilla, dry ingredients and sour cream. Drop by teaspoons.

title: outdoor apple dumplings
directions: Mix apple pie filling with 2/3 cup water in large skillet with a tight cover.
When apples come to boiling, cut biscuits into quarters (use scissors).
Let pieces drop on bubbling apples. Sprinkle biscuits with cinnamon and sugar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
No fair peeking, but biscuits will pop up like dumplings.
Serve at once with cream.

title: hidden valley ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes (or if you prefer peel).
Cut into small pieces.
Place in large saucepan and cover with water.
Boil until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain water.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Whip with electric mixer or hand potato masher until smooth.
If too thick add more milk.

title: french silk dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Blend all 3 ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish.
Lay bacon pieces on top.
Cover.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli-chicken
directions: Wash chicken; drain.
Brown chicken in butter on stove until done, then add broccoli and the soup.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.

title: cream cheese tortilla wrap
directions: Mix cheese, chilies and olives well.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas.
Roll up and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve with salsa dip.

title: spicy pumpkin cake
directions: Combine cake mix and soda, then proceed by package directions, substituting pumpkin for 1/2 the liquid.
Fold in dates and nuts. Bake as directed. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: cantaloupe ice cream
directions: Heat whole milk and can milk on low; remove when warm.
Add sugar and set aside.
Beat eggs slightly and add to the milk (I use a whisk; it works well).
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a large ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend together all but the shrimp.
Mix well and add shrimp. Let chill about an hour.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of glass pie plate. Layer other ingredients on top in order listed.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
You may also put in microwave at High power for about 7 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: fudge
directions: Put milk, sugar and margarine into saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and immediately add the other ingredients.
Stir until chips are smooth.
Pour into buttered, square dish and allow to cool until firm.

title: dried fruit spice bars
directions: Combine raisins, dates, prunes and water.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Add oil.
Cool, add egg.
In large bowl put all dry ingredients, spices, vanilla and nuts.
Mix with fruit.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and spread in greased baking dish.
Combine margarine, mushroom soup and cheese in skillet.
Heat until smooth.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Pepperidge Farm dressing mix (dry) over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strada
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain and set aside.
Unroll each half of crescent rolls, making a rectangle.
Line bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of slightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Press rectangle seams securely to seal.
Sprinkle sausage over dough and top with shredded cheese and green pepper.
Combine eggs and remaining ingredients and pour over casseroles.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour
and cocoa.	Add milk and egg yolks. Cook until
thick,
stirring
constantly.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine thoroughly.
Add flour and continue to mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Shape into cakes.
Fry quickly until brown.

title: rich pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add eggs, milk and butter. Stir only until ingredients are blended (the batter will be lumpy). Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: stewed venison
directions: Cut roast up into small cubes.
Place venison, 2 onions, bay leaves, vinegar and enough water to cover in a large bowl.
Soak for 3 hours.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cherry filling.
Pour into pie shell and chill until firm, then spread filling on top.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook for 2 hours.
Mix 1/2 cup cornstarch with water and stir in.
Can up.

title: southern fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in well sprayed loaf pan.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Heat cheese in top of double boiler.
When soft, add all other ingredients and heat well.
Serve hot with toast points.
Serves 12.

title: cookies 'n kahlua
directions: Combine Kahlua and milk in a shallow bowl or pan.
Dip cookies into mixture and remove (do not soak until soggy!).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a long pan or two pie pans greased with melted bacon grease. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, mustard and pepper.
Layer chilies and cheese in an 8-inch square or round casserole.
Pour egg-milk mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Halve chicken breasts and wrap in bacon.
Cover bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish with chipped beef.
Place chicken on top.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs and melted butter together and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together, put in casserole dish, put dish in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Put breadcrumb mixture over top of casserole
and bake at 350° for 45 mins. or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; let set 1 hour to marinate. Then add to broccoli, cheese and bacon.
Should stand for 6 to 8 hours for the flavors to blend.

title: 8 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Add each ingredient a layer at a time.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool in refrigerator until firm, then slice into 2 x 2-inch or 2 x 3-inch squares.
This is a very rich cookie.
Happy eating!

title: mints
directions: Cream together the sugar and cream cheese.
Dip a toothpick into the oil of peppermint and then into the batter.
Repeat 3 times.
Add food coloring the same way.
If not the color you wish, add more times.

title: sausage egg brunch
directions: Break bread up into pieces and put in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put sausage over bread and then sprinkle cheese on top. Mix eggs and milk together and pour mixture over bread and meat. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° until cheese comes to top.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: I'd like to live with you.
I'll be very little bother.
I need just a spot in your refrigerator and, if you'll feed me 1 cup flour, 1 cup milk and 1/2 cup sugar each Wednesday and Saturday, I'll live a long time.
Do not use me the day you feed me; take out what you need before.
Never let me get down to less than 1 cup before feeding.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in an electric mixer.
Blend until smooth.
Set aside.
Drain grated cucumber on paper towels, gently squeezing out excess moisture.
Fold into cream cheese mixture. Cut bread with cookie cutters into desired shapes.
Spread mixture on shapes.
Garnish with cucumber wedges, fresh dill, parsley, etc.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Blend ingredients.
Bake at 350° until well done.
Straw comes out clean.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix and bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet hot meatballs
directions: Mix raw meat, garlic powder, salt, pepper and chopped onion together and make into meatballs.
Brown meatballs.
Mix picante and cranberry sauces together and heat until cranberry sauce melts.
Add meatballs and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: apples and cool whip
directions: Slice apples on plate with Cool Whip on side.
Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Dip in Cool Whip and eat.
Enjoy!!

title: queen of heart salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: lemon lush
directions: *Make as directions on package.
For variations, use cherry or blueberry pie filling.
